1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:15,281
Right now, it's Girls' Generation!

2
00:00:15,348 --> 00:00:18,018
-We're here with Tiffany and Hyo-yeon.
-Yes.

3
00:00:18,084 --> 00:00:22,022
Hyo-yeon is a huge fan of the show
who watches it on repeat.

4
00:00:22,088 --> 00:00:25,458
-And she's here today because of someone.
-So she is.

5
00:00:26,459 --> 00:00:27,460
It must be Chef Jong-won.

6
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:29,529
Someone on the show is her ideal type.

7
00:00:29,596 --> 00:00:31,931
-Among the cast members?
-Yes.

8
00:00:31,998 --> 00:00:33,666
-I don't even have my hopes up.
-Who is it?

9
00:00:33,733 --> 00:00:35,268
It's none other than…

10
00:00:35,335 --> 00:00:36,603
-Yes?
-None other than?

11
00:00:36,669 --> 00:00:37,937
It's none other than

12
00:00:38,004 --> 00:00:39,172
Jung-hwan.

13
00:00:40,507 --> 00:00:41,741
Jung-hwan.

14
00:00:41,808 --> 00:00:42,976
Me?

15
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:44,911
-I'm not one of the chefs.
-It's Jung-hwan?

16
00:00:44,978 --> 00:00:46,079
Here's the reason.

17
00:00:46,146 --> 00:00:48,281
I like someone who's reserved

18
00:00:48,348 --> 00:00:49,749
-and on the serious side.
-What?

19
00:00:49,816 --> 00:00:50,950
-What?
-That's not him at all.

20
00:00:51,017 --> 00:00:52,585
-She doesn't know him.
-He's the opposite.

21
00:00:52,652 --> 00:00:54,554
Someone who doesn't act frivolously.

22
00:00:54,821 --> 00:00:55,889
WHAT NOW?

23
00:00:56,256 --> 00:00:57,991
THAT GUY?

24
00:00:58,058 --> 00:00:59,526
-Wait a second.
-What do you mean?

25
00:00:59,859 --> 00:01:02,162
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

26
00:01:02,996 --> 00:01:04,831
SERIOUSNESS?

27
00:01:04,898 --> 00:01:06,866
I watched everything
from <i>Cook Representative</i>

28
00:01:06,933 --> 00:01:08,835
to <i>Buddy Into the Wild, </i>even the reruns.

29
00:01:08,902 --> 00:01:11,337
I also watched every season
of <i>The Gentlemen's League.</i>

30
00:01:11,404 --> 00:01:12,939
-Really?
-She's a serious fan.

31
00:01:13,006 --> 00:01:14,741
When he's with us,

32
00:01:14,808 --> 00:01:16,609
he's not really the reserved type.

33
00:01:16,676 --> 00:01:18,011
When someone falls,

34
00:01:18,078 --> 00:01:20,580
he's usually the first
to run over and trample on them.

35
00:01:20,647 --> 00:01:22,382
VANGUARD OF RUNNING OVER
AND TRAMPLING ON THEM

36
00:01:22,449 --> 00:01:24,350
Excuse me, Chef Choi.

37
00:01:24,417 --> 00:01:26,286
-"Chef Choi."
-Then what?

38
00:01:26,352 --> 00:01:28,822
I have to run the show as a host,
so I can't just sit quietly.

39
00:01:28,888 --> 00:01:29,856
I must do my job.

40
00:01:29,923 --> 00:01:33,159
Running a show is different
from attacking and mocking.

41
00:01:33,860 --> 00:01:34,694
Soccer Player Ahn.

42
00:01:35,095 --> 00:01:38,031
TIT FOR TAT

43
00:01:38,098 --> 00:01:40,867
Do you like any of our chefs?
They're all great cooks.

44
00:01:40,934 --> 00:01:42,535
-Among the chefs here?
-Yes.

45
00:01:42,602 --> 00:01:45,405
-Sam is pretty reserved.
-Yes, he's reserved.

46
00:01:45,472 --> 00:01:46,840
He hasn't said a word today.

47
00:01:46,906 --> 00:01:48,441
-Look at him now.
-Not a single word.

48
00:01:48,508 --> 00:01:50,376
He hasn't said a word

49
00:01:50,443 --> 00:01:52,245
-to get on your good side.
-He's so reserved.

50
00:01:52,312 --> 00:01:55,048
But is he also witty?
I know he is when he cooks,

51
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:56,783
but I don't know what he's usually like.

52
00:01:56,850 --> 00:01:59,319
-He's really talkative.
-He could be the host.

53
00:01:59,519 --> 00:02:01,087
REALLY?

54
00:02:01,154 --> 00:02:02,689
He's the host in the green room.

55
00:02:02,755 --> 00:02:03,890
NODS

56
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:05,358
-He talks so much.
-He's the host.

57
00:02:05,425 --> 00:02:06,893
ONLY THE CHEFS GET TO SEE HIM EMCEE

58
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:08,461
He goes on a roll.

59
00:02:08,528 --> 00:02:10,463
That's why he doesn't talk much here.

60
00:02:10,530 --> 00:02:11,898
He's already exhausted.

61
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:13,766
So please keep an eye on Sam too.

62
00:02:14,033 --> 00:02:16,803
LOOK FORWARD TO SPOTTING
HIS UNEXPECTED CHARM

63
00:02:16,870 --> 00:02:18,972
There's something to celebrate
for Girls' Generation.

64
00:02:19,038 --> 00:02:21,674
<i>Next year already marks</i>
<i>their 20th anniversary!</i>

65
00:02:21,975 --> 00:02:23,343
THAT'S AMAZING

66
00:02:23,409 --> 00:02:24,844
-Yes.
-It's amazing.

67
00:02:24,911 --> 00:02:28,781
You've returned as a group
during your 15th anniversary.

68
00:02:28,848 --> 00:02:31,684
So if you were to prepare
for your 20th year,

69
00:02:31,751 --> 00:02:33,653
shouldn't you be
planning something already?

70
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:34,621
-Right…
-Right?

71
00:02:34,687 --> 00:02:37,090
Yes, we should start planning now.

72
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:38,224
-What?
-Yes.

73
00:02:38,291 --> 00:02:40,460
Tiffany is in charge of planning.

74
00:02:40,527 --> 00:02:42,762
Is that so? Does she usually do it?

75
00:02:42,829 --> 00:02:45,064
She's meticulous, prepared

76
00:02:45,131 --> 00:02:46,533
-and a born leader.
-She is?

77
00:02:46,599 --> 00:02:49,669
She's also great
at keeping the members under control.

78
00:02:49,736 --> 00:02:51,237
So she has leadership.

79
00:02:51,304 --> 00:02:52,438
-I see.
-Hey.

80
00:02:52,505 --> 00:02:54,374
We already have plans.

81
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:55,942
-Do you have plans?
-Sorry?

82
00:02:56,009 --> 00:02:57,777
-She says you do.
-We do?

83
00:02:57,844 --> 00:02:59,913
-She says you have plans.
-We already have plans.

84
00:02:59,979 --> 00:03:01,948
-She got you.
-She's saying you made plans.

85
00:03:02,015 --> 00:03:03,349
Let me share something here.

86
00:03:03,416 --> 00:03:05,518
She rarely reads the group chat.

87
00:03:06,252 --> 00:03:07,887
AHEM…

88
00:03:07,954 --> 00:03:10,623
-No.
-From what we heard,

89
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:12,425
Hyo-yeon is known

90
00:03:12,492 --> 00:03:15,395
-as the worst communicator in the group.
-I see.

91
00:03:15,461 --> 00:03:16,763
What's going on?

92
00:03:16,829 --> 00:03:20,433
-I can't agree, but let me hear her out.
-Let's hear her out.

93
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:22,101
There may be a misunderstanding.

94
00:03:22,168 --> 00:03:23,870
When I send something,

95
00:03:23,937 --> 00:03:27,874
I believe she should give me an answer
at least within 48 hours.

96
00:03:28,141 --> 00:03:29,075
EVERYONE AGREES

97
00:03:29,142 --> 00:03:31,277
-Only then can we move forward.
-Right.

98
00:03:31,344 --> 00:03:33,346
You must collect opinions
to move things forward.

99
00:03:33,413 --> 00:03:35,782
But Hyo-yeon never checks the group chat.

100
00:03:35,848 --> 00:03:36,983
Some people just close it

101
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:39,419
when they see that
there are too many words.

102
00:03:39,485 --> 00:03:41,020
I feel that. When I see too many words,

103
00:03:41,087 --> 00:03:42,922
-I don't want to read it.
-What?

104
00:03:43,223 --> 00:03:45,124
SO CONFIDENT

105
00:03:45,191 --> 00:03:46,559
If I have 300 messages to read,

106
00:03:46,626 --> 00:03:49,662
I try to figure out the key points
and only read those.

107
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:51,464
But many times,
I don't get the right points.

108
00:03:51,531 --> 00:03:53,666
At your 15th anniversary press conference,

109
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:55,935
something shocking happened, right?

110
00:03:56,002 --> 00:03:57,637
-What happened?
-Before the press conference

111
00:03:57,704 --> 00:04:00,206
for our 15th anniversary,

112
00:04:00,273 --> 00:04:03,109
I told everyone to dress in neutral colors

113
00:04:03,176 --> 00:04:07,580
such as black, white,
or something toned down

114
00:04:07,647 --> 00:04:10,516
since the backdrop will be hot pink.

115
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:12,252
But Hyo-yeon showed up

116
00:04:12,318 --> 00:04:15,054
in a hot pink outfit.

117
00:04:15,121 --> 00:04:16,489
Let's take a look at the picture.

118
00:04:16,556 --> 00:04:17,924
-Dang it.
-Let's check.

119
00:04:17,991 --> 00:04:19,058
Will we only see her head?

120
00:04:19,125 --> 00:04:20,727
The backdrop was hot pink, but…

121
00:04:20,793 --> 00:04:22,061
GIGGLING

122
00:04:22,128 --> 00:04:23,963
She's chroma keying.

123
00:04:24,030 --> 00:04:25,031
The backdrop was hot pink…

124
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:28,368
HYO-YEON'S HERE

125
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:30,536
She already told her
that the backdrop will be hot pink.

126
00:04:30,603 --> 00:04:31,638
CAMOUFLAGE

127
00:04:31,704 --> 00:04:34,841
But Hyo-yeon showed up in hot pink.

128
00:04:34,907 --> 00:04:37,577
I was the most flustered on that day.

129
00:04:37,644 --> 00:04:40,813
-Right?
-"Why is the backdrop hot pink?"

130
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,982
-She mentioned it, though.
-But you missed it.

131
00:04:43,049 --> 00:04:46,185
I only noticed the key word, "hot pink."

132
00:04:46,252 --> 00:04:47,920
MISCOMMUNICATION

133
00:04:47,987 --> 00:04:50,590
So I told my stylist
that I needed a hot pink outfit.

134
00:04:50,657 --> 00:04:52,258
-"Wear it and come."
-Yes. "I need to wear hot pink."

135
00:04:52,325 --> 00:04:54,560
That's why I'm wearing
the hottest pink in the picture.

136
00:04:54,627 --> 00:04:57,363
Did you not want to be in the picture?

137
00:04:57,430 --> 00:04:59,599
-It was like a green screen.
-To dress like that?

138
00:04:59,666 --> 00:05:01,200
We were the flustered ones.

139
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:03,102
We finally released an album
after five years.

140
00:05:04,170 --> 00:05:05,004
You're right.

141
00:05:05,071 --> 00:05:08,808
It's been five years, and you can only see
her face, arms, and feet. Look.

142
00:05:08,875 --> 00:05:10,877
Now, in case I don't get her answer,

143
00:05:10,943 --> 00:05:14,681
I make a very simple poll
with multiple options

144
00:05:14,747 --> 00:05:17,350
so the members can just choose one
before the deadline.

145
00:05:17,417 --> 00:05:19,919
I learned a lot from watching her.

146
00:05:19,986 --> 00:05:21,554
So these days,

147
00:05:21,621 --> 00:05:23,423
I make sure I vote in time.

148
00:05:23,690 --> 00:05:25,191
SHE'S A NEW WOMAN

149
00:05:25,258 --> 00:05:26,693
Yes, you do that these days.

150
00:05:26,759 --> 00:05:28,428
I've been doing my best to pay attention,

151
00:05:28,494 --> 00:05:30,430
but I'm sorry that I'm late.

152
00:05:30,963 --> 00:05:32,765
A SWEET APOLOGY

153
00:05:32,832 --> 00:05:34,434
-"I'm sorry that I'm late."
-I think

154
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:37,236
our 20th anniversary will go well,
thanks to <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

155
00:05:37,537 --> 00:05:39,872
I'M SORRY!

156
00:05:39,939 --> 00:05:41,974
In celebration of their 20th anniversary,

157
00:05:42,041 --> 00:05:44,477
Hyo-yeon has been painting
a bigger picture.

158
00:05:44,544 --> 00:05:47,747
-It's Project Girls' Generation-HRS.
-The hottest.

159
00:05:47,814 --> 00:05:50,717
-It's so funny.
-Before, there was Girls' Generation-TTS.

160
00:05:50,783 --> 00:05:52,218
-Yes.
-Girls' Generation-TTS.

161
00:05:52,285 --> 00:05:54,854
Taeyeon, Tiffany, and Seohyun
had formed a vocal unit.

162
00:05:54,921 --> 00:05:56,189
But it's now our time,

163
00:05:56,255 --> 00:05:57,924
so I wanted to make something.

164
00:05:57,990 --> 00:06:00,693
I thought I should be the main vocalist,
not the dancer.

165
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:01,861
A different side of you.

166
00:06:01,928 --> 00:06:04,764
But Tiffany played a part
in building up the project.

167
00:06:05,198 --> 00:06:06,599
TTS VS. HRS

168
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:08,801
-Let's watch a video clip together.
-Okay.

169
00:06:09,435 --> 00:06:10,570
This is so funny.

170
00:06:10,636 --> 00:06:11,838
HRS.

171
00:06:11,904 --> 00:06:14,841
<i>-I saw this.</i>
-I want to do something for the 20th year.

172
00:06:14,907 --> 00:06:17,443
-<i>There's TTS, so I can do</i>
-She's there with Hyo-yeon.

173
00:06:17,510 --> 00:06:18,544
<i>HRS.</i>

174
00:06:18,611 --> 00:06:19,879
<i>"HRS"?</i>

175
00:06:19,946 --> 00:06:21,347
<i>So are you the Taeyeon of that unit?</i>

176
00:06:21,914 --> 00:06:23,282
<i>I'm Taeyeon.</i>

177
00:06:23,983 --> 00:06:25,151
So this happened?

178
00:06:25,218 --> 00:06:26,786
<i>I'm sorry. I can't keep a straight face.</i>

179
00:06:26,853 --> 00:06:28,821
<i>I'll give you a noogie</i>
<i>if you say "Oh, my God" again.</i>

180
00:06:29,088 --> 00:06:30,523
A FUNNY (NOOGIE) TIME

181
00:06:30,857 --> 00:06:33,092
HRS, A NEW UNIT TO CHALLENGE TTS

182
00:06:33,159 --> 00:06:34,360
<i>They got together.</i>

183
00:06:35,428 --> 00:06:36,896
<i>Is there a song</i>

184
00:06:36,963 --> 00:06:39,198
<i>that'll make TTS bothered by us?</i>

185
00:06:39,265 --> 00:06:40,233
<i>There's "Holler."</i>

186
00:06:40,299 --> 00:06:41,200
<i>"Holler" sounds good.</i>

187
00:06:41,267 --> 00:06:44,036
-We're having the public vote for us.
-With this song?

188
00:06:44,103 --> 00:06:45,471
Go with "Holler," then.

189
00:06:45,538 --> 00:06:48,040
<i>-You three are serious.</i>
-Hello, I'm Hyo-yeon of HRS.

190
00:06:48,107 --> 00:06:50,276
I'll begin my main vocalist audition now.

191
00:06:50,343 --> 00:06:52,412
CRAZY AD LIBS

192
00:06:54,414 --> 00:06:55,948
EVEN THEY CAN'T KEEP A STRAIGHT FACE

193
00:06:56,015 --> 00:06:57,283
She's cracking up in the back.

194
00:06:57,350 --> 00:06:58,651
BIRTH OF HRS'S MAIN VOCALIST
THAT TAEYEON (MAY NOT) ACKNOWLEDGE

195
00:06:58,718 --> 00:06:59,786
EXPLOSIVE ATTENTION
3.65M VIEWS

196
00:06:59,852 --> 00:07:00,787
<i>It was a huge hit.</i>

197
00:07:00,853 --> 00:07:03,089
THE LEAGUE OF THEIR OWN CONTINUES…

198
00:07:03,756 --> 00:07:06,492
So have you come to a decision?
Or is this still ongoing?

199
00:07:06,559 --> 00:07:08,161
It's still ongoing.

200
00:07:08,227 --> 00:07:09,562
It's a sensitive topic among us,

201
00:07:09,629 --> 00:07:11,864
so we haven't been discussing this.

202
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:13,966
WILL THERE BE A UNIT TO STAND AGAINST TTS?

203
00:07:14,033 --> 00:07:16,135
She's serious about this.

204
00:07:16,202 --> 00:07:17,804
I keep getting greatly inspired by her.

205
00:07:17,870 --> 00:07:19,205
-Yes.
-So we should also make

206
00:07:19,272 --> 00:07:20,773
a unit called The Mice.

207
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:22,108
The Micey?

208
00:07:22,175 --> 00:07:24,310
Jong-won, I, and Kyun should

209
00:07:24,377 --> 00:07:26,846
-make a unit called SonSukKyun.
-SonSukKyun?

210
00:07:26,913 --> 00:07:28,281
-SonSukKyun?
-SonSukKyun?

211
00:07:28,347 --> 00:07:30,883
-It sounds familiar.
-Son Suk-ku might get offended.

212
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:32,218
Jong-won is the main vocalist,

213
00:07:32,285 --> 00:07:33,686
I'm the instrumentalist,

214
00:07:33,753 --> 00:07:36,522
and Kyun is the dancer. Just like that.

215
00:07:36,589 --> 00:07:38,324
We can be wedding singers
called SonSukKyun.

216
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:39,959
THE BRIDE IN MAY IS PLEASED

217
00:07:40,026 --> 00:07:41,327
-SonSukKyun.
-My gosh.

218
00:07:41,394 --> 00:07:43,529
The three of us have something too.

219
00:07:43,596 --> 00:07:45,398
-They have something.
-Go. I'm Ho.

220
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:47,867
-Ho, Nam, Sung.
-Ho, Nam, Sung.

221
00:07:47,934 --> 00:07:49,502
-HoNamSung.
-We're HoNamSung.

222
00:07:49,569 --> 00:07:51,471
-I like that name.
-SonSukKyun and HoNamSung.

223
00:07:51,537 --> 00:07:53,606
It sounds like you could do well
for a Chinese audience too.

224
00:07:53,673 --> 00:07:55,708
They sound reliable.

225
00:07:55,775 --> 00:07:59,445
They could stand against HRS,
and the name sticks too.

226
00:07:59,512 --> 00:08:01,747
Why don't you let Sam
be a part of something like this?

227
00:08:01,814 --> 00:08:03,583
-Let him in.
-Yes, let him join you.

228
00:08:03,649 --> 00:08:05,051
SamPoong…

229
00:08:05,117 --> 00:08:07,620
SamPoongJa.

230
00:08:07,687 --> 00:08:09,522
-Ja? Why Ja?
-The crazy one, <i>doreun-ja</i>.

231
00:08:11,057 --> 00:08:13,259
"Ja? Why am I Ja?"

232
00:08:13,326 --> 00:08:14,861
THE BRIDE-TO-BE LOST HER NAME

233
00:08:14,927 --> 00:08:16,395
I won't allow this after May.

234
00:08:16,462 --> 00:08:18,531
THE BRIDE IN MAY WILL ALLOW IT
ONLY UNTIL MAY

235
00:08:18,598 --> 00:08:21,667
It's now time to check out
Hyo-yeon's fridge.

236
00:08:21,734 --> 00:08:24,136
I was surprised to hear this
from our production crew.

237
00:08:24,203 --> 00:08:26,672
When they went to pick up her fridge,

238
00:08:26,739 --> 00:08:28,774
they went to Girls' Generation's dorm.

239
00:08:28,841 --> 00:08:32,845
-She's still using the fridge in her dorm.
-She is?

240
00:08:32,912 --> 00:08:35,114
So you've been there for 19 years,
even after everyone left?

241
00:08:35,181 --> 00:08:36,415
Yes.

242
00:08:36,716 --> 00:08:38,084
THAT'S AMAZING

243
00:08:38,150 --> 00:08:41,420
She's keeping the heritage alive.

244
00:08:41,487 --> 00:08:42,722
My family lives in Songdo,

245
00:08:42,788 --> 00:08:45,424
but in order to do my job
more conveniently,

246
00:08:45,491 --> 00:08:46,893
I needed that comfortable shelter.

247
00:08:46,959 --> 00:08:49,795
Also, I get meals prepared
to keep me from starving.

248
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:51,364
You can't find a better place to live.

249
00:08:51,430 --> 00:08:53,633
-Yes, she's practical.
-Right?

250
00:08:53,699 --> 00:08:56,936
Back in the day,
when Sunny visited the show,

251
00:08:57,003 --> 00:09:00,673
<i>she told us that the fridge</i>
<i>was from your dorm.</i>

252
00:09:00,740 --> 00:09:02,308
-Yes, we lived together then.
-We were there.

253
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:05,111
She uses this alone,
but it's also from their dorm.

254
00:09:05,177 --> 00:09:06,612
Do you manage it yourself, though?

255
00:09:06,679 --> 00:09:08,648
Yes, and when I crave something,

256
00:09:08,714 --> 00:09:11,551
sometimes I tell the housekeeper
and she gets it for me.

257
00:09:11,617 --> 00:09:14,387
Is she someone
who has always worked with you?

258
00:09:14,453 --> 00:09:16,322
Since our middle school days.

259
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:19,258
She was there even before
Girls' Generation was formed.

260
00:09:19,325 --> 00:09:22,194
She was our first dorm housekeeper.

261
00:09:22,261 --> 00:09:23,963
-Since your trainee days?
-Yes.

262
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:24,864
How long has it been?

263
00:09:24,931 --> 00:09:27,199
-Twenty-two years?
-Yes, twenty-two years.

264
00:09:27,266 --> 00:09:30,503
-How did that happen?
-She's more than family.

265
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:33,673
-She must've fed you longer than your mom.
-She fed her more than her mother.

266
00:09:33,739 --> 00:09:34,640
She's practically her mom.

267
00:09:34,707 --> 00:09:38,210
Hyo-yeon lives alone,
but this is the fridge from their dorm.

268
00:09:38,277 --> 00:09:40,446
-We present her fridge!
-Fridge!

269
00:09:40,513 --> 00:09:41,747
-Fridge!
-Fridge!

270
00:09:41,814 --> 00:09:43,015
HUH?

271
00:09:43,082 --> 00:09:44,984
Is it because she lives alone?
It's pretty empty.

272
00:09:45,051 --> 00:09:46,218
-We present her fridge!
-Fridge!

273
00:09:46,285 --> 00:09:47,987
PRESENTING HYO-YEON'S FRIDGE

274
00:09:48,054 --> 00:09:51,424
-It has that dorm fridge vibe.
-It does.

275
00:09:51,490 --> 00:09:53,626
-One second.
-Take a look and see how different it is

276
00:09:53,693 --> 00:09:55,194
from the time
when other members were there.

277
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:57,530
The last time we saw the dorm fridge,

278
00:09:57,597 --> 00:09:59,765
the food had labels with names on them.

279
00:09:59,832 --> 00:10:01,500
-You're right.
-Yes.

280
00:10:01,567 --> 00:10:04,003
-We used colored Post-it notes.
-Color-coded.

281
00:10:04,070 --> 00:10:07,106
My housekeeper makes me food
when I'm in Korea.

282
00:10:07,173 --> 00:10:09,742
-Only a little when you're here.
-After seeing your schedule.

283
00:10:09,809 --> 00:10:12,979
Now, I see some side dishes.

284
00:10:13,045 --> 00:10:15,748
Those are the dishes
I've always had since I was younger.

285
00:10:16,015 --> 00:10:17,183
REMINISCING

286
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:19,118
Look at this.

287
00:10:19,185 --> 00:10:21,320
-I like <i>jang-jorim</i>, a braised side dish.
-You do.

288
00:10:21,387 --> 00:10:23,189
It's salty and nice.

289
00:10:23,255 --> 00:10:25,391
Is this your housekeeper's egg omelet?

290
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:28,094
That's the way she makes it.

291
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:30,062
-The housekeeper's omelet.
-Yes!

292
00:10:30,129 --> 00:10:31,030
SQUEAL

293
00:10:31,097 --> 00:10:34,900
-Yolks on the outside, whites inside.
-She separated the yolks and whites?

294
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:35,901
She made layers.

295
00:10:35,968 --> 00:10:38,437
But the best one there
is the seasoned dried squid.

296
00:10:38,504 --> 00:10:41,140
-This one?
-It's not tough at all. It's very tender.

297
00:10:41,207 --> 00:10:44,210
-This?
-I can finish a bowl of rice with that.

298
00:10:44,276 --> 00:10:46,545
One of the tabs is broken.

299
00:10:46,612 --> 00:10:48,014
ONE TAB DESTROYED

300
00:10:48,247 --> 00:10:49,315
FLUSHED

301
00:10:49,382 --> 00:10:50,483
You can see that it isn't new.

302
00:10:50,549 --> 00:10:52,184
-It's been 20 years.
-Yes, right.

303
00:10:52,251 --> 00:10:53,886
-She's thrifty.
-She is.

304
00:10:53,953 --> 00:10:56,822
How do you usually eat? And around when?

305
00:10:56,889 --> 00:10:58,858
I eat my first meal a little later

306
00:10:58,924 --> 00:11:00,760
around 12 p.m. to 1 p.m.

307
00:11:00,826 --> 00:11:02,595
I really like natto, so…

308
00:11:02,662 --> 00:11:04,030
-Natto?
-Yes.

309
00:11:04,096 --> 00:11:07,633
I eat a simple breakfast
by mixing two fried eggs, natto,

310
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:10,036
two spoonfuls of soy sauce,
and a dash of sesame oil on rice.

311
00:11:10,102 --> 00:11:12,905
-I also eat natto for breakfast.
-When I crave something lighter,

312
00:11:12,972 --> 00:11:14,974
I grind Chinese yam, apple, and milk.

313
00:11:15,041 --> 00:11:16,342
I see.

314
00:11:16,409 --> 00:11:18,144
-What about dinner?
-Dinner?

315
00:11:18,210 --> 00:11:19,745
I almost always eat out.

316
00:11:19,812 --> 00:11:22,715
I like to find good places to eat at,
and most recently,

317
00:11:22,782 --> 00:11:25,117
I've been hooked on <i>sundae-gukbap,</i>
blood sausage soup and rice.

318
00:11:25,284 --> 00:11:26,118
OLD MAN REACTION

319
00:11:26,185 --> 00:11:27,386
I went all the way to Cheongnyangni

320
00:11:27,453 --> 00:11:30,423
to a famous joint called Gohyangjib.
I like to eat there,

321
00:11:30,489 --> 00:11:31,824
and I go to Gunja often too.

322
00:11:31,891 --> 00:11:33,125
-Gunja.
-It's called Haemi's.

323
00:11:33,192 --> 00:11:35,261
That place also makes
delicious <i>sundae-gukbap.</i>

324
00:11:35,327 --> 00:11:37,096
Don't you love <i>sundae-guk?</i>

325
00:11:37,163 --> 00:11:38,964
-I love <i>sundae-guk.</i>
-Right? Me too.

326
00:11:39,031 --> 00:11:42,001
-Hapjeong Sundae-guk is good.
-Where is it?

327
00:11:42,068 --> 00:11:43,669
-By the rotary.
-Right!

328
00:11:43,736 --> 00:11:46,205
-It's pretty famous.
-Yes, that place is good.

329
00:11:46,272 --> 00:11:47,940
Once you're hooked, you only eat that.

330
00:11:48,007 --> 00:11:49,408
I only go after one thing.

331
00:11:49,475 --> 00:11:53,512
Once she's hooked,
she spends months eating just that.

332
00:11:53,579 --> 00:11:55,481
Until that restaurant
goes out of business.

333
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:57,917
-She's like me.
-It's a wonder.

334
00:11:57,983 --> 00:11:59,685
You're still like that?

335
00:11:59,752 --> 00:12:00,820
I'm still like what?

336
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:03,723
HYO-YEON, YOU STILL EAT THE SAME WAY

337
00:12:03,789 --> 00:12:04,957
I see.

338
00:12:06,659 --> 00:12:07,793
That's the way she eats.

339
00:12:07,860 --> 00:12:09,528
Do you like to add lots of chili sauce?

340
00:12:09,595 --> 00:12:11,464
I like to add spicy Cheongyang pepper…

341
00:12:11,530 --> 00:12:12,665
WHOA

342
00:12:12,732 --> 00:12:14,834
-…with a pile of perilla powder.
-Perilla powder.

343
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:16,435
-So it tastes nutty.
-It is nutty.

344
00:12:16,502 --> 00:12:18,137
-She eats like an old dude.
-She does.

345
00:12:18,204 --> 00:12:22,007
-She has it. She has perilla powder here.
-I do.

346
00:12:22,074 --> 00:12:25,277
Did your housekeeper
leave this in here for you?

347
00:12:25,344 --> 00:12:26,979
I got it at the marketplace.

348
00:12:27,446 --> 00:12:30,416
THE PERILLA POWDER SHE BOUGHT HERSELF

349
00:12:30,483 --> 00:12:32,218
Do you eat Western cuisine?

350
00:12:32,284 --> 00:12:33,886
Western cuisine?

351
00:12:33,953 --> 00:12:35,554
I grill sirloin from time to time.

352
00:12:35,621 --> 00:12:36,789
-That's not Western cuisine.
-Sirloin?

353
00:12:36,856 --> 00:12:38,390
"That's not Western cuisine"?

354
00:12:38,457 --> 00:12:39,925
Grilling sirloin.

355
00:12:39,992 --> 00:12:42,094
-You're mostly into Korean cuisine, then.
-I am.

356
00:12:42,161 --> 00:12:45,297
I found some smoked chicken.

357
00:12:45,364 --> 00:12:46,665
-Hey.
-I love that product.

358
00:12:46,732 --> 00:12:48,334
-Isn't it good?
-So good. The whole leg.

359
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:49,468
She has five bags.

360
00:12:49,535 --> 00:12:53,072
-It's a perfect beer snack.
-It's so good.

361
00:12:53,139 --> 00:12:56,008
Around 10 or 11 o'clock in the night,

362
00:12:56,075 --> 00:12:58,177
I always crave some beer.

363
00:12:58,244 --> 00:13:01,547
I used to order lots of delivery food,

364
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:03,516
then I put on some weight.

365
00:13:03,582 --> 00:13:05,751
So I now eat those or canned tuna

366
00:13:05,818 --> 00:13:07,253
when I drink beer.

367
00:13:07,319 --> 00:13:08,487
-With beer?
-Yes.

368
00:13:08,554 --> 00:13:10,623
What's in here? Vegetables.

369
00:13:10,689 --> 00:13:12,291
-Cilantro.
-Yes.

370
00:13:12,358 --> 00:13:13,559
Water parsley.

371
00:13:13,626 --> 00:13:16,695
I really love vegetables that have
a strong scent.

372
00:13:16,762 --> 00:13:19,698
-She has a bunch of cilantro.
-Cilantro and crown daisy.

373
00:13:19,765 --> 00:13:21,333
What's lemongrass?

374
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,968
-Lemongrass?
-Lemongrass?

375
00:13:23,035 --> 00:13:25,104
-Isn't she the first to have it?
-Lemongrass?

376
00:13:25,171 --> 00:13:27,873
I love Southeast Asian food,
such as tom yum soup.

377
00:13:27,940 --> 00:13:29,508
-You need this to make that dish.
-Yes.

378
00:13:29,575 --> 00:13:31,043
So I bought those,

379
00:13:31,110 --> 00:13:33,512
but I have no idea what to do with them.

380
00:13:33,579 --> 00:13:35,481
You can't eat them raw, can you?

381
00:13:35,548 --> 00:13:38,651
<i>-You usually make soup with them.</i>
<i>-You have to make broth or soup with them.</i>

382
00:13:38,717 --> 00:13:40,820
-Now that I'm here…
-It's pretty tough to use.

383
00:13:40,886 --> 00:13:43,656
…I thought the chefs could use them
to make something delicious.

384
00:13:44,456 --> 00:13:45,991
What are these?

385
00:13:46,058 --> 00:13:47,326
-Okra.
-Okra.

386
00:13:47,393 --> 00:13:49,895
-Okra? She has okra?
-Okra?

387
00:13:49,962 --> 00:13:51,564
What's this vegetable?

388
00:13:51,630 --> 00:13:53,465
It has a slimy texture,

389
00:13:53,532 --> 00:13:55,601
which I like a lot.

390
00:13:55,668 --> 00:13:57,503
-Like Chinese yams.
-She likes Chinese yams too.

391
00:13:57,570 --> 00:13:58,437
Right.

392
00:13:58,504 --> 00:14:00,606
Japanese people love those, don't they?

393
00:14:00,673 --> 00:14:01,607
Tell them. Hurry.

394
00:14:01,674 --> 00:14:05,144
First, rub the surface with some salt,

395
00:14:05,211 --> 00:14:06,879
then boil it lightly.

396
00:14:06,946 --> 00:14:09,548
It'll create a nice texture
and lots of slime,

397
00:14:09,615 --> 00:14:10,916
which helps with digestion.

398
00:14:10,983 --> 00:14:12,718
It was also good when grilled.

399
00:14:12,785 --> 00:14:14,854
Yes, it's nice when grilled
or even deep-fried.

400
00:14:16,222 --> 00:14:18,557
Where have we seen these before?
Whose fridge was it?

401
00:14:18,624 --> 00:14:20,226
Someone else liked these.

402
00:14:20,292 --> 00:14:22,228
-Jang Keun-suk.
-It was Keun-suk.

403
00:14:22,294 --> 00:14:24,430
-Thai chili.
-Yes, Thai chili.

404
00:14:24,496 --> 00:14:25,531
Do you like spicy food?

405
00:14:25,598 --> 00:14:27,132
I love it.

406
00:14:27,199 --> 00:14:29,869
There's this Thai sauce
called <i>prik nam pla.</i>

407
00:14:29,935 --> 00:14:31,503
-<i>Prik nam pla.</i>
-Yes.

408
00:14:31,570 --> 00:14:34,406
I really love that.
Chili dipped in fish sauce.

409
00:14:34,473 --> 00:14:36,942
There are times
when Cheongyang pepper just isn't enough.

410
00:14:37,009 --> 00:14:38,344
She likes her food spicy.

411
00:14:38,410 --> 00:14:39,511
Next, the freezer.

412
00:14:39,578 --> 00:14:40,479
Whoa!

413
00:14:40,546 --> 00:14:43,082
-There they are.
-There they are. The freezer.

414
00:14:43,148 --> 00:14:45,517
-What are those?
-The insides?

415
00:14:52,524 --> 00:14:54,627
-What's that?
-This is <i>sundae</i>, blood sausage.

416
00:14:54,693 --> 00:14:56,395
-What's that?
-Hog maw.

417
00:14:56,462 --> 00:14:58,597
-Hog maw?
-Hog maw?

418
00:14:58,664 --> 00:15:00,733
-That looks good.
-That's really good.

419
00:15:00,799 --> 00:15:02,968
Is this hog maw? Offal.

420
00:15:03,702 --> 00:15:05,170
PREVIOUSLY

421
00:15:05,738 --> 00:15:06,839
I CAN'T EAT WHAT'S INSIDE

422
00:15:09,008 --> 00:15:11,343
-Offal. That's hog maw.
-I see.

423
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:12,811
Do you make <i>sundae</i> dishes at home?

424
00:15:12,878 --> 00:15:15,981
I've been going out
to eat <i>sundae-guk</i> often these days,

425
00:15:16,048 --> 00:15:18,984
-and I especially love <i>abai sundae</i>.
-It says <i>abai sundae</i>, Hamgyeong-do style.

426
00:15:19,051 --> 00:15:21,954
I ordered one too many,
so I don't know what to do with them.

427
00:15:22,021 --> 00:15:23,489
Right, these are…

428
00:15:23,555 --> 00:15:24,390
chicken gizzards.

429
00:15:24,456 --> 00:15:26,058
-Gizzards.
-Chicken stomach.

430
00:15:26,125 --> 00:15:28,427
-I like those.
-Chicken gizzards.

431
00:15:28,794 --> 00:15:30,930
WHAT ON EARTH IS THAT?

432
00:15:30,996 --> 00:15:33,299
My favorite gizzard dish is stir-fry.

433
00:15:33,365 --> 00:15:36,168
I like to stir-fry those
with garlic, black pepper, and salt.

434
00:15:36,235 --> 00:15:38,804
I wanted to make some at home

435
00:15:38,871 --> 00:15:40,539
-so I bought some.
-I have a question.

436
00:15:42,308 --> 00:15:43,575
"WHY" BY TAEYEON

437
00:15:43,642 --> 00:15:45,477
The texture is really nice,

438
00:15:45,544 --> 00:15:46,645
and it's low in calories.

439
00:15:46,712 --> 00:15:49,348
-It's high in protein and low on calories.
-Good texture too.

440
00:15:52,051 --> 00:15:53,986
That's my dog's favorite.

441
00:15:54,053 --> 00:15:55,354
HAHA

442
00:15:55,521 --> 00:15:57,289
COME ON

443
00:15:59,425 --> 00:16:01,460
Your dog must enjoy the texture.

444
00:16:01,527 --> 00:16:03,128
Of course, dogs chew.

445
00:16:03,195 --> 00:16:05,230
-I always keep some in my freezer.
-Always?

446
00:16:05,297 --> 00:16:07,499
It's kind of like dog chew.

447
00:16:07,566 --> 00:16:10,002
She has meat on the second shelf.

448
00:16:10,069 --> 00:16:11,337
-Beef.
-Beef.

449
00:16:11,403 --> 00:16:13,105
Is this pork?

450
00:16:13,172 --> 00:16:15,474
-Some shrimps too.
-Yes.

451
00:16:15,541 --> 00:16:19,678
You can always buy the ones
that are already prepped, can't you?

452
00:16:19,745 --> 00:16:22,381
I don't think prepped shrimps

453
00:16:22,448 --> 00:16:23,515
are real shrimps.

454
00:16:24,516 --> 00:16:27,753
Because the flavor
is all in the shrimp head.

455
00:16:28,020 --> 00:16:30,189
MY FRIEND IS SO FEISTY

456
00:16:30,255 --> 00:16:31,857
Shrimp head is the real deal.

457
00:16:31,924 --> 00:16:33,625
Do you eat shrimp heads?

458
00:16:33,692 --> 00:16:35,561
I do.

459
00:16:35,627 --> 00:16:40,432
I get raw shrimp, prep them,
peel them, and eat them.

460
00:16:40,499 --> 00:16:42,901
I see. It has a distinct smell.

461
00:16:42,968 --> 00:16:44,770
-It has a rich flavor.
-A rich flavor.

462
00:16:44,837 --> 00:16:46,305
She truly is a carnivore.

463
00:16:46,372 --> 00:16:47,940
-Me?
-A carnivore?

464
00:16:48,007 --> 00:16:49,475
-A carnivore? Come on.
-I mean…

465
00:16:49,541 --> 00:16:51,710
It sounds so aggressive.

466
00:16:51,777 --> 00:16:52,811
Head,

467
00:16:52,878 --> 00:16:53,846
heads,

468
00:16:53,912 --> 00:16:55,180
offal…

469
00:16:55,247 --> 00:16:56,749
You two have incompatible tastes.

470
00:16:56,815 --> 00:16:58,150
How did you two live together?

471
00:16:58,217 --> 00:17:01,186
-How did you spend 20 years together?
-I don't know.

472
00:17:01,253 --> 00:17:03,188
Next, shelf-stable ingredients.

473
00:17:03,255 --> 00:17:05,190
This stands out. What's this?

474
00:17:05,257 --> 00:17:07,693
I recently craved some soup curry,

475
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:10,462
so I got some
on my recent trip to Sapporo.

476
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:11,864
I see. Hokkaido.

477
00:17:12,431 --> 00:17:13,665
-What's this sauce?
-Sambal.

478
00:17:13,732 --> 00:17:15,734
-Another spicy sauce.
-Sambal.

479
00:17:15,801 --> 00:17:17,269
That's a good one.

480
00:17:17,336 --> 00:17:20,172
Among our recent guests, she seems to have

481
00:17:20,239 --> 00:17:22,107
-the most extraordinary taste in food.
-She does.

482
00:17:22,174 --> 00:17:23,709
It's just like mine.

483
00:17:23,776 --> 00:17:25,778
That's all for Hyo-yeon's fridge!

484
00:17:25,844 --> 00:17:27,780
DONE CHECKING OUT HYO-YEON'S FRIDGE

485
00:17:29,048 --> 00:17:31,817
What kind of dishes
is she looking for today?

486
00:17:31,884 --> 00:17:34,119
Let's find out her orders.

487
00:17:34,186 --> 00:17:35,921
Show us. Hyo-yeon's orders.

488
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:38,524
Lost in the Scent, Holler.

489
00:17:38,590 --> 00:17:39,558
We got both at once.

490
00:17:39,625 --> 00:17:42,261
The second one is Drunk on Beer, Holler.

491
00:17:42,327 --> 00:17:44,630
-Holler!
-Holler! It's the song.

492
00:17:44,696 --> 00:17:46,331
The aspiring main vocalist.

493
00:17:46,665 --> 00:17:48,367
HER ASPIRATION SHOWS IN THE ORDERS

494
00:17:48,434 --> 00:17:49,435
Please tell us more.

495
00:17:49,501 --> 00:17:52,304
I really enjoy dishes
that have a strong scent,

496
00:17:52,371 --> 00:17:56,041
those that make you smell like the food
when you're done with it.

497
00:17:57,509 --> 00:17:59,178
Like, "Hey, you had <i>cheonggukjang</i>."

498
00:17:59,244 --> 00:18:01,680
NOT THE EXAMPLE I WAS THINKING OF, BUT…

499
00:18:01,747 --> 00:18:04,550
You always smell like <i>sundae-guk</i>
after you eat it.

500
00:18:04,616 --> 00:18:06,251
-You always smell like <i>sundae</i>.
-Yes.

501
00:18:06,318 --> 00:18:08,921
-It can feel like a fragrance.
-That fragrance.

502
00:18:08,987 --> 00:18:11,890
When I travel abroad,
at times, I remember the place

503
00:18:11,957 --> 00:18:15,727
by the scent of a particular dish
and even revisit because of that.

504
00:18:15,794 --> 00:18:17,062
It's that memorable for me.

505
00:18:17,129 --> 00:18:19,631
I want to remember today
with the scent of the dishes

506
00:18:19,698 --> 00:18:21,467
the chefs make for me.

507
00:18:21,533 --> 00:18:25,671
I want something with a strong scent.

508
00:18:25,737 --> 00:18:27,372
She'll remember the scent and remember us.

509
00:18:27,439 --> 00:18:29,708
-That's nice.
-That's the kind of dish she wants.

510
00:18:29,775 --> 00:18:30,976
Drunk on Beer, Holler.

511
00:18:31,043 --> 00:18:35,380
Beer snacks are the most important to me.

512
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:38,350
Today, I want something
really rich and heavy.

513
00:18:38,417 --> 00:18:39,718
I'll lose weight on my own,

514
00:18:39,785 --> 00:18:41,253
so don't mind that.

515
00:18:41,320 --> 00:18:43,255
-Make something really intense.
-An intense dish.

516
00:18:43,322 --> 00:18:45,257
-A beer snack.
-Intense beer snack.

517
00:18:45,324 --> 00:18:47,826
I have a huge portion
of <i>sundae </i>and hog maw,

518
00:18:47,893 --> 00:18:48,961
so please use those too.

519
00:18:49,027 --> 00:18:51,430
-She's asking you to use those.
-My mouth is watering.

520
00:18:51,497 --> 00:18:53,866
Now, the four people
who didn't go last week,

521
00:18:53,932 --> 00:18:56,602
Hyun-suk, Poong, Ho-young, and Nam-no.

522
00:18:56,668 --> 00:18:58,604
Who's up first? Nam-no?

523
00:18:58,670 --> 00:19:01,607
As someone who also ends the day
with a glass of beer,

524
00:19:01,673 --> 00:19:03,775
I'll join Drunk on Beer, Holler.

525
00:19:03,842 --> 00:19:05,444
-The beer snack.
-Holler!

526
00:19:05,511 --> 00:19:07,946
-It suits him.
-Do "holler" properly. One more time.

527
00:19:08,514 --> 00:19:10,315
Drunk on Beer, Holler!

528
00:19:10,649 --> 00:19:11,984
PLEASED

529
00:19:12,050 --> 00:19:13,452
You get the next pick, Hyun-suk.

530
00:19:14,319 --> 00:19:17,356
-Instead of a heavy dish…
-Rock-paper-scissors?

531
00:19:17,422 --> 00:19:21,326
…I want to make something
that'll make you get lost in the scent.

532
00:19:21,393 --> 00:19:23,495
-The scent, then.
-Yes.

533
00:19:23,562 --> 00:19:27,399
Nam-no and Hyun-suk
have gone their separate ways.

534
00:19:27,466 --> 00:19:29,034
I see.

535
00:19:29,101 --> 00:19:30,369
DROOLING OVER NAM-NO AND BEER

536
00:19:30,435 --> 00:19:32,771
Look at Poong. He's like a hyena.

537
00:19:32,838 --> 00:19:34,239
My gosh.

538
00:19:34,306 --> 00:19:37,843
Bar snacks are pretty much my specialty.

539
00:19:37,910 --> 00:19:39,945
-Stop it.
-And that's why…

540
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:43,115
-I'll go with Lost in the Scent, Holler.
-I see.

541
00:19:43,182 --> 00:19:44,917
Are you going easy on Nam-no?

542
00:19:44,983 --> 00:19:47,519
Yes, I'll let him off today.

543
00:19:47,586 --> 00:19:49,521
-You have to win, okay?
-Thank you.

544
00:19:49,588 --> 00:19:51,089
That means I have to lose.

545
00:19:51,156 --> 00:19:53,992
-Ho-young is placed automatically.
-The beer snack.

546
00:19:54,059 --> 00:19:57,396
And now, the round
that'll make her feel lost in the scent,

547
00:19:57,462 --> 00:20:01,066
Hyun-suk and Poong's round will begin!

548
00:20:01,366 --> 00:20:02,634
LET'S BEGIN NOW, HOLLER

549
00:20:03,202 --> 00:20:04,336
<i>Holler</i>

550
00:20:04,403 --> 00:20:09,041
<i>This is the first round played</i>
<i>with Hyo-yeon's ingredients.</i>

551
00:20:09,107 --> 00:20:10,809
Lost in the Scent…

552
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:11,777
<i>Holler</i>

553
00:20:12,077 --> 00:20:14,546
DANCING AUTOMATICALLY

554
00:20:15,714 --> 00:20:17,015
This round is between

555
00:20:17,082 --> 00:20:21,119
a man who seems to be drunk on himself,
Chef Choi Hyun-suk,

556
00:20:21,186 --> 00:20:22,921
and a guy who just seems drunk,

557
00:20:22,988 --> 00:20:24,489
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong.

558
00:20:24,556 --> 00:20:27,492
THE HANGOVER MATCH
CHOI HYUN-SUK VS. KIM POONG

559
00:20:27,559 --> 00:20:30,095
Last week,
during the cook-offs for Tiffany,

560
00:20:30,162 --> 00:20:33,532
Chef Jong-won became the sole first place.

561
00:20:33,599 --> 00:20:38,203
But if Poong wins this round,
he'll rise up to joint first place.

562
00:20:38,270 --> 00:20:39,738
-He's on fire.
-Poong's magic

563
00:20:39,805 --> 00:20:43,108
has been working smoothly lately.
He's doing so well.

564
00:20:43,175 --> 00:20:45,844
Long ago,
when he failed to make what he wanted,

565
00:20:45,911 --> 00:20:47,613
-not only was it inedible…
-Right.

566
00:20:47,679 --> 00:20:49,982
-…but it also gave people stomachaches.
-Stomachaches?

567
00:20:50,048 --> 00:20:52,251
-Did anyone end up at the hospital?
-You already know that.

568
00:20:52,317 --> 00:20:54,486
Stop making up stuff.

569
00:20:54,820 --> 00:20:56,054
OF COURSE, WE'RE JOKING

570
00:20:56,121 --> 00:20:58,490
But now, even when the recipe
doesn't go his way,

571
00:20:58,557 --> 00:20:59,958
the guests all seem to enjoy it.

572
00:21:00,025 --> 00:21:01,560
<i>Kim Poong magic</i>

573
00:21:02,060 --> 00:21:04,763
THE DISHES LOOK RUINED, BUT…

574
00:21:04,830 --> 00:21:06,832
I don't think you even have to try it.

575
00:21:07,299 --> 00:21:08,734
STREAMS OF COMPLIMENTS

576
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:10,969
A TOUCHING TRUE STORY

577
00:21:11,036 --> 00:21:13,105
-Why do they go well?
-I wonder why.

578
00:21:13,171 --> 00:21:15,841
Poong has recently changed once again.

579
00:21:15,907 --> 00:21:18,610
He has twice as many stars
compared to Chef Hyun-suk.

580
00:21:18,944 --> 00:21:21,480
HOW THE TIMES HAVE CHANGED

581
00:21:21,546 --> 00:21:24,416
-You're right. I didn't know.
-He doesn't have as many stars.

582
00:21:24,483 --> 00:21:26,051
-He only has two stars?
-Please.

583
00:21:26,118 --> 00:21:28,153
-So smug.
-He's so smug.

584
00:21:28,220 --> 00:21:30,956
A Korean saying goes, "Even a dog
picks things up after three years."

585
00:21:31,023 --> 00:21:32,724
And this dog right here

586
00:21:32,791 --> 00:21:34,559
has been around for ten years.

587
00:21:34,626 --> 00:21:35,961
You're right.

588
00:21:36,028 --> 00:21:37,696
We have a green room recording.

589
00:21:37,763 --> 00:21:39,965
Poong said this about Hyun-suk.

590
00:21:40,032 --> 00:21:42,734
"If he wants to beat me,
he'd better go back to the basics."

591
00:21:44,703 --> 00:21:47,439
-The basics?
-You said something like that.

592
00:21:47,506 --> 00:21:49,241
When he first started,

593
00:21:49,308 --> 00:21:51,109
he had that incredibly sharp energy.

594
00:21:51,176 --> 00:21:53,278
<i>He always scared me with his energy</i>

595
00:21:53,345 --> 00:21:54,980
and even made me wet my pants.

596
00:21:55,047 --> 00:21:57,015
He used to have that effect.

597
00:21:57,082 --> 00:21:59,551
He used to overwhelm everyone
with one look.

598
00:21:59,618 --> 00:22:02,220
-He did.
-When his younger colleagues got cheeky,

599
00:22:02,287 --> 00:22:03,755
he used to glare like this.

600
00:22:03,822 --> 00:22:05,190
Now, he's like, "Just destroy me."

601
00:22:05,257 --> 00:22:06,892
He even said that.

602
00:22:06,958 --> 00:22:08,794
He'd offer his arm and his leg.

603
00:22:09,127 --> 00:22:10,429
SELF-SACRIFICING

604
00:22:10,495 --> 00:22:13,832
Chef Hyun-suk said
he felt especially confident

605
00:22:13,899 --> 00:22:15,400
about the order Hyo-yeon made.

606
00:22:15,467 --> 00:22:17,736
Those who make perfumes
are called perfumers.

607
00:22:17,803 --> 00:22:20,339
And I was nicknamed the Perfumer Chef.

608
00:22:20,405 --> 00:22:22,841
-Really?
-I've never heard that before.

609
00:22:22,908 --> 00:22:24,042
-It's news to me.
-Me too.

610
00:22:24,109 --> 00:22:25,444
-Delicious…
-I've never heard of it.

611
00:22:25,510 --> 00:22:27,346
-…and beautiful…
-Aren't nicknames widely known?

612
00:22:27,412 --> 00:22:28,880
THE GLARE FROM THE PAST

613
00:22:28,947 --> 00:22:33,085
He needs to look in order for me
to subdue him with my eyes. Look at me.

614
00:22:33,151 --> 00:22:34,486
I don't want to.

615
00:22:34,820 --> 00:22:36,688
OVERPOWERING COMPLETED

616
00:22:36,755 --> 00:22:39,358
I like to build the first scent,
the second, the third, and the last

617
00:22:39,424 --> 00:22:41,526
into the recipe through calculation.

618
00:22:41,593 --> 00:22:42,928
So it wouldn't make any sense

619
00:22:42,994 --> 00:22:46,198
for me to lose against someone
who makes no calculations

620
00:22:46,264 --> 00:22:48,400
and cooks without knowing the basics
like this guy.

621
00:22:48,467 --> 00:22:50,168
-Yes, that's crazy.
-He's feisty.

622
00:22:50,235 --> 00:22:53,271
Poong, do you take the scent
into consideration when you cook?

623
00:22:53,338 --> 00:22:55,941
I'm also nicknamed
the Perfumer Webtoon Artist.

624
00:22:56,007 --> 00:22:57,776
THE PERFUMER WEBTOON ARTIST?

625
00:22:57,843 --> 00:22:59,644
I also do stuff like

626
00:22:59,711 --> 00:23:01,113
the finishing scent or whatever.

627
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,048
PICKING UP LINES, NOT TECHNIQUES

628
00:23:03,115 --> 00:23:05,951
-"The finishing scent or whatever"?
-You do?

629
00:23:06,017 --> 00:23:09,388
-Yes, I know I can do this.
-He just throws random things out there.

630
00:23:10,222 --> 00:23:12,424
CHEF HYUN-SUK'S INGREDIENTS:
LEMONGRASS, CILANTRO, OKRA

631
00:23:12,491 --> 00:23:14,393
SHRIMP, WHITE WINE,
ORANGE VINEGAR, CHILI SAUCE

632
00:23:14,459 --> 00:23:17,195
First up, Chef Hyun-suk.
What are you making?

633
00:23:17,262 --> 00:23:19,564
The name of my dish is

634
00:23:19,631 --> 00:23:22,300
Senior No. 55.

635
00:23:22,801 --> 00:23:24,236
-What?
-What now?

636
00:23:24,302 --> 00:23:26,538
-Chanel No. 55.
-Chanel No. 55?

637
00:23:26,605 --> 00:23:27,773
-Did you say Chanel?
-No.

638
00:23:27,839 --> 00:23:30,709
-Senior No. 55.
-Senior.

639
00:23:30,776 --> 00:23:32,177
-Senior?
-Senior No. 55.

640
00:23:32,244 --> 00:23:33,278
Not Chanel.

641
00:23:33,345 --> 00:23:34,780
Isn't he 55 years old?

642
00:23:37,482 --> 00:23:39,785
Like that. He said it like that.

643
00:23:39,851 --> 00:23:42,220
This 55-year-old chef will make

644
00:23:42,287 --> 00:23:45,724
a dish that is like perfume just for her.

645
00:23:45,791 --> 00:23:47,559
A dish like perfume.

646
00:23:47,626 --> 00:23:49,528
I'm making a type of soufflé

647
00:23:49,594 --> 00:23:51,730
by steaming the dish.

648
00:23:51,797 --> 00:23:54,065
It could feel like Chinese dim sum,

649
00:23:54,132 --> 00:23:56,435
but I'll serve it with Western sauces.

650
00:23:56,501 --> 00:24:00,639
I'll make a stylish
and a fragrant perfume-like dish.

651
00:24:00,705 --> 00:24:01,840
LOOK FORWARD TO IT!

652
00:24:02,674 --> 00:24:04,709
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S INGREDIENTS:
WATER PARSLEY, HOG MAW

653
00:24:04,776 --> 00:24:06,845
SHRIMP, CHERRY TOMATO, THAI CHILI,
SAMBAL, TSUYU, LEMON JUICE

654
00:24:06,912 --> 00:24:09,748
Up against Hyun-suk is Poong.
What are you making?

655
00:24:09,815 --> 00:24:12,951
Here's the name of the dish
I'm making today.

656
00:24:13,018 --> 00:24:14,820
Hyun-suk, Way to Go!

657
00:24:15,654 --> 00:24:17,222
-Hyun-suk, Way to Go!
-Yes.

658
00:24:17,289 --> 00:24:19,291
It's our song called "Way to Go."

659
00:24:19,357 --> 00:24:20,659
-Yes.
-It didn't sound like it.

660
00:24:21,059 --> 00:24:22,060
A NAME TO IRRITATE HYUN-SUK

661
00:24:22,127 --> 00:24:24,896
-It's Hyun-suk, Way to Go.
-Hyun-suk, Way to Go.

662
00:24:24,963 --> 00:24:27,566
There are many different scents.

663
00:24:27,632 --> 00:24:31,369
But I love the scent
of water parsley very much,

664
00:24:31,436 --> 00:24:35,073
so I thought it'd be nice
to maximize its smell.

665
00:24:35,140 --> 00:24:37,576
There's a dish called <i>pon goong,</i>

666
00:24:37,642 --> 00:24:39,878
which is often had in Thailand and Laos.

667
00:24:39,945 --> 00:24:44,783
<i>It's a mix of cooked and mashed shrimp,</i>
<i>fish sauce, spicy chili, and more,</i>

668
00:24:44,850 --> 00:24:46,084
<i>then it's ground to a paste.</i>

669
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:49,321
It's like a dip you eat with rice or meat.

670
00:24:49,387 --> 00:24:51,890
I'll pound water parsley into it
and maximize the scent,

671
00:24:51,957 --> 00:24:54,926
and serve the dip
with water parsley <i>jeon</i>, pancake,

672
00:24:54,993 --> 00:24:56,061
for you to have together.

673
00:24:56,127 --> 00:24:57,762
I'll make a dish…

674
00:24:57,829 --> 00:24:59,564
-It sounds good.
-…full of water parsley scent.

675
00:24:59,631 --> 00:25:01,833
-It sounds good.
-All right.

676
00:25:01,900 --> 00:25:04,336
And now, let us begin the cook-off.

677
00:25:04,402 --> 00:25:07,339
He's here to teach a lesson
to the dog who picked up a few things.

678
00:25:07,405 --> 00:25:10,141
The schoolteacher of the show,
Chef Choi Hyun-suk.

679
00:25:10,742 --> 00:25:13,612
-But this guy is here to bite Hyun-suk.
-He looks like a nutria.

680
00:25:13,678 --> 00:25:17,015
Been with <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> for a decade,
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong.

681
00:25:17,315 --> 00:25:18,517
LOVES HIS STUNTS

682
00:25:18,583 --> 00:25:21,052
It's a round between
the natural enemies of the show.

683
00:25:21,119 --> 00:25:23,355
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

684
00:25:23,421 --> 00:25:24,589
Okay!

685
00:25:26,825 --> 00:25:29,394
THE SCHOOLTEACHER VERSUS THE SCHOOL DOG

686
00:25:29,961 --> 00:25:32,964
Chef Hyun-suk must be astonished
at how much things have changed.

687
00:25:33,031 --> 00:25:33,865
Meringue?

688
00:25:34,432 --> 00:25:35,433
STARTING WITH A WHIPPING MACHINE

689
00:25:35,500 --> 00:25:38,003
I guess Chef Hyun-suk
has lost much of his energy.

690
00:25:38,069 --> 00:25:40,038
He used to whip meringue by hand,

691
00:25:40,105 --> 00:25:41,640
-but he's using a machine.
-He does now.

692
00:25:41,706 --> 00:25:44,643
-Until recently, he did it by hand.
-By hand.

693
00:25:44,709 --> 00:25:46,511
And he lost that round.

694
00:25:46,578 --> 00:25:48,213
He found out that we have the machine.

695
00:25:48,280 --> 00:25:49,347
You, be quiet.

696
00:25:49,414 --> 00:25:50,248
ME? HEHE

697
00:25:50,515 --> 00:25:52,083
EVERYONE LIKES TO TEASE THE TEACHER

698
00:25:52,918 --> 00:25:54,920
Webtoon Artist Poong begins with shrimps.

699
00:25:54,986 --> 00:25:56,988
-It's so slippery.
-By hand.

700
00:25:57,055 --> 00:25:59,991
You shouldn't throw away the heads.

701
00:26:00,058 --> 00:26:01,826
You can deep-fry these later.

702
00:26:01,893 --> 00:26:02,894
I'll set them aside.

703
00:26:02,961 --> 00:26:04,529
-So you aren't using the heads?
-No.

704
00:26:04,596 --> 00:26:07,232
-Hyo-yeon said she likes the heads.
-She did.

705
00:26:07,299 --> 00:26:08,767
That part tastes savory.

706
00:26:08,833 --> 00:26:11,803
I can't help it, though.
I only need the meat for this dish.

707
00:26:12,304 --> 00:26:13,672
WHAT'S THE WHIPPING TEACHER DOING?

708
00:26:13,738 --> 00:26:15,140
IS IT DONE?

709
00:26:15,607 --> 00:26:16,908
TESTING THE MERINGUE

710
00:26:16,975 --> 00:26:18,343
"The meringue I whipped."

711
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:20,078
"The meringue I whipped"?

712
00:26:20,145 --> 00:26:22,847
-"The meringue I whipped is solid."
-"My meringue."

713
00:26:24,282 --> 00:26:25,951
THE STATUE OF MERINGUE

714
00:26:26,451 --> 00:26:28,320
It should've fallen out.

715
00:26:28,386 --> 00:26:30,255
-Right?
-It should've fallen out

716
00:26:30,322 --> 00:26:32,857
-and made his hair white.
-White?

717
00:26:33,191 --> 00:26:34,426
TRYING NOT TO LAUGH

718
00:26:34,492 --> 00:26:35,460
CONFUSED

719
00:26:35,527 --> 00:26:38,763
I think he got the steps mixed up
while focusing on the meringue.

720
00:26:38,830 --> 00:26:41,032
-He's using shrimps.
-Shrimps.

721
00:26:41,099 --> 00:26:42,500
What's glaring at me going to do?

722
00:26:42,567 --> 00:26:43,969
He's glaring charismatically.

723
00:26:44,035 --> 00:26:46,605
Be my guest and charge at me.
You only get 15 minutes.

724
00:26:46,671 --> 00:26:47,939
Charge at me. Come at me.

725
00:26:48,239 --> 00:26:49,641
STUDENTS AT THIS SCHOOL NUKES EACH OTHER

726
00:26:49,708 --> 00:26:52,744
Come at me. You have time.

727
00:26:52,811 --> 00:26:54,679
-He's provoking him.
-Be quiet.

728
00:26:55,647 --> 00:26:56,481
Prepping shrimps.

729
00:26:56,548 --> 00:26:58,350
THEY BOTH BEGIN TO PREP SHRIMPS!

730
00:26:58,416 --> 00:27:00,919
It looks like Poong is faster
at peeling shrimps.

731
00:27:01,419 --> 00:27:02,587
You're right.

732
00:27:03,288 --> 00:27:04,589
Yes, he's right.

733
00:27:04,656 --> 00:27:06,424
He's much faster.

734
00:27:06,491 --> 00:27:07,859
MUST YOU POINT THAT OUT?

735
00:27:07,926 --> 00:27:09,060
He's glaring at Ho-young too.

736
00:27:09,127 --> 00:27:10,829
Poong peeled them quickly.

737
00:27:11,396 --> 00:27:13,865
He's now losing against him.

738
00:27:13,932 --> 00:27:16,768
-He's using shrimps to…
-He's mincing them.

739
00:27:16,835 --> 00:27:18,236
Oh, my. That's dangerous.

740
00:27:18,303 --> 00:27:20,972
-Be careful.
-He used to do it too fast for us to see.

741
00:27:21,873 --> 00:27:23,274
He's copying Chef Jong-won.

742
00:27:23,341 --> 00:27:25,944
SON JONG-WON'S TECHNIQUE WITH GOOD VIBES

743
00:27:26,011 --> 00:27:27,112
He's doing that?

744
00:27:27,178 --> 00:27:28,647
He's copying Jong-won now.

745
00:27:28,713 --> 00:27:30,415
He's supposed to use two knives.

746
00:27:30,482 --> 00:27:32,550
His knife moves too fast for us to see.

747
00:27:32,617 --> 00:27:36,087
But he can't chop them
as finely as he could back then.

748
00:27:36,154 --> 00:27:38,623
There's no need to chop them finely.
I need some texture.

749
00:27:38,690 --> 00:27:40,225
That was intentional.

750
00:27:40,291 --> 00:27:41,393
1. MIX SHRIMP AND GARLIC

751
00:27:41,693 --> 00:27:42,527
SHOOTING SALT!

752
00:27:44,496 --> 00:27:45,864
OLD CREATOR CREW!

753
00:27:46,931 --> 00:27:48,533
He seasons it with salt.

754
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:50,769
It would be insane to see Poong win again.

755
00:27:51,970 --> 00:27:53,538
CHOPPING WATER PARSLEY INTO LARGE PIECES

756
00:27:53,605 --> 00:27:54,572
Water parsley.

757
00:27:54,639 --> 00:27:56,808
-Poong preps water parsley.
-Water parsley.

758
00:27:56,875 --> 00:27:58,576
-In a mortar.
-The water parsley?

759
00:27:58,643 --> 00:28:00,478
That's going to bring out more scent.

760
00:28:01,279 --> 00:28:02,681
-Because it's bruised.
-Yes.

761
00:28:03,982 --> 00:28:06,685
Poong only focuses on his dish right now.

762
00:28:08,687 --> 00:28:11,022
Look at him bopping his head.

763
00:28:11,089 --> 00:28:12,924
2. POUND BOILED SHRIMP WITH WATER PARSLEY

764
00:28:12,991 --> 00:28:14,759
-You're pounding them together?
-With water parsley?

765
00:28:14,993 --> 00:28:15,927
OHO

766
00:28:15,994 --> 00:28:17,395
I'm pounding the shrimps with it.

767
00:28:18,029 --> 00:28:19,564
He's pounding the shrimps?

768
00:28:19,631 --> 00:28:21,933
He's pounding them with fish sauce.

769
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,501
Thai chili, right?

770
00:28:23,568 --> 00:28:25,804
And fish sauce.
He's making it a bit spicy.

771
00:28:25,870 --> 00:28:27,238
Yes, it has to be spicy.

772
00:28:27,305 --> 00:28:28,440
Don't add too much.

773
00:28:28,506 --> 00:28:29,407
More?

774
00:28:29,474 --> 00:28:31,876
-Not too much.
-Not too much.

775
00:28:31,943 --> 00:28:34,312
-Don't let it be too spicy.
-Not too much.

776
00:28:34,379 --> 00:28:35,346
Not too much?

777
00:28:35,413 --> 00:28:37,148
-Is that okay?
-It's fine by me.

778
00:28:37,415 --> 00:28:38,583
NO, NOT YOU…

779
00:28:38,650 --> 00:28:41,286
-I'm okay with it.
-It's not for you.

780
00:28:41,352 --> 00:28:43,655
-Not too much?
-No, that's good.

781
00:28:44,222 --> 00:28:45,590
It needs Cheongyang pepper too.

782
00:28:46,658 --> 00:28:48,460
-It looks so spicy.
-It looks quite spicy.

783
00:28:48,526 --> 00:28:49,427
Don't overdo it.

784
00:28:49,494 --> 00:28:53,431
-It's okay. Don't worry about it.
-He's putting lots of work into the sauce.

785
00:28:53,498 --> 00:28:54,466
My mouth is watering.

786
00:28:54,532 --> 00:28:56,101
She has to perform on stage, so…

787
00:28:56,167 --> 00:28:57,702
You're worried about my restroom business?

788
00:28:57,769 --> 00:28:58,837
Yes.

789
00:28:58,903 --> 00:29:01,239
-He's adding cherry tomatoes too.
-Cherry tomatoes?

790
00:29:01,306 --> 00:29:02,340
He's adding cherry tomatoes.

791
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:04,309
It'll make it milder and add umami.

792
00:29:04,375 --> 00:29:07,512
That sauce already looks so tasty.

793
00:29:07,979 --> 00:29:10,115
THE SCHOOLTEACHER LOST
ALL HIS ATTENTION TO THE DOG

794
00:29:10,849 --> 00:29:15,587
2. MIX SEASONED SHRIMP
WITH OKRA AND MERINGUE

795
00:29:15,653 --> 00:29:18,223
-That looks really good.
-I should remember the recipe.

796
00:29:19,057 --> 00:29:20,125
GUYS!

797
00:29:21,426 --> 00:29:22,360
ATTENTION, PLEASE!

798
00:29:22,827 --> 00:29:24,362
THE SCHOOLTEACHER'S KNIFE DANCE!

799
00:29:24,662 --> 00:29:26,331
LOOK AT HIM GO

800
00:29:26,397 --> 00:29:29,667
He mixed meringue, salt, and okra.

801
00:29:29,734 --> 00:29:31,736
He's buttering the Teflon sheet.

802
00:29:31,803 --> 00:29:33,238
It's a sheet.

803
00:29:33,304 --> 00:29:36,708
He put the egg whites into a mold
to make a shape.

804
00:29:37,642 --> 00:29:40,011
Chef Hyun-suk is shaping the egg.

805
00:29:41,846 --> 00:29:43,848
SHOWING OFF THE MERINGUE HE HEAPED UP

806
00:29:43,915 --> 00:29:46,217
He shows it off and steams it.

807
00:29:46,284 --> 00:29:48,553
-He's trying to keep it in that shape.
-Yes.

808
00:29:48,820 --> 00:29:50,421
POONG IS STILL WORKING ON THE SAUCE

809
00:29:50,488 --> 00:29:53,158
-That's the sauce.
-Some sambal.

810
00:29:53,224 --> 00:29:54,826
-And a bit of <i>tsuyu</i>.
-<i>Tsuyu</i>.

811
00:29:54,893 --> 00:29:56,194
SUGAR

812
00:29:56,261 --> 00:29:57,896
-And lemon juice.
-Lemon juice.

813
00:29:57,962 --> 00:29:59,764
It looks like it'll be very fragrant.

814
00:30:00,031 --> 00:30:01,866
SQUIRTING A GENEROUS AMOUNT!

815
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:04,335
It probably smells
a lot like Southeast Asian food.

816
00:30:04,402 --> 00:30:06,337
That must be the sauce
for the water parsley <i>jeon</i>.

817
00:30:06,404 --> 00:30:08,139
Yes, that's right.

818
00:30:09,207 --> 00:30:11,042
What's that? Hog maw?

819
00:30:11,109 --> 00:30:12,977
He's boiling hog maw.

820
00:30:13,044 --> 00:30:14,012
Hog maw?

821
00:30:14,245 --> 00:30:15,847
WHAT'S HE USING TO FIGHT THE HOG MAW?

822
00:30:16,414 --> 00:30:17,315
LEMONGRASS

823
00:30:17,382 --> 00:30:18,883
He's using that much lemongrass?

824
00:30:20,552 --> 00:30:21,486
That much?

825
00:30:21,553 --> 00:30:22,687
A HUGE BOWL OF FRAGRANCE

826
00:30:22,954 --> 00:30:24,189
AND ON TOP OF THAT!

827
00:30:24,923 --> 00:30:26,157
CILANTRO SPIKE!

828
00:30:27,292 --> 00:30:28,426
FLUTTER…

829
00:30:28,693 --> 00:30:29,894
STRIKING THE AIR

830
00:30:29,961 --> 00:30:32,697
Hyun-suk spikes!

831
00:30:32,764 --> 00:30:34,732
-He'll need another shoulder surgery.
-Yes.

832
00:30:35,099 --> 00:30:36,734
STOP TRYING TOO HARD…

833
00:30:42,240 --> 00:30:44,542
Is that cilantro?

834
00:30:44,609 --> 00:30:46,477
He's still going strong.

835
00:30:46,544 --> 00:30:48,880
-Cilantro?
-Cilantro and lemongrass.

836
00:30:48,947 --> 00:30:49,814
Is that cilantro?

837
00:30:49,881 --> 00:30:51,349
-He's blending them.
-Cilantro.

838
00:30:51,416 --> 00:30:53,618
-Cilantro and lemongrass.
-It already smells strong.

839
00:30:53,685 --> 00:30:55,286
-Is that vinegar?
-Vinegar?

840
00:30:55,353 --> 00:30:56,821
-Cooking wine.
-Cooking wine.

841
00:30:57,355 --> 00:31:00,925
I guess that's the sauce.

842
00:31:00,992 --> 00:31:02,260
I can smell it.

843
00:31:02,327 --> 00:31:04,329
I can smell it all the way from here.

844
00:31:04,395 --> 00:31:06,197
-It smells strong.
-Yes, I can smell it too.

845
00:31:06,264 --> 00:31:09,434
The scent of Chef Hyun-suk's dish
will probably come from that sauce.

846
00:31:09,500 --> 00:31:10,435
MAXIMIZE THE SCENT BY BLENDING

847
00:31:10,869 --> 00:31:12,837
WHIRRRR

848
00:31:12,904 --> 00:31:14,572
If you're done, can you turn it off?

849
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:17,909
-Mister!
-We can't hear anything!

850
00:31:17,976 --> 00:31:18,843
It's too loud.

851
00:31:18,910 --> 00:31:20,278
-Hey, Choi!
-It's so loud.

852
00:31:20,345 --> 00:31:22,547
-Sir, can you turn that off?
-Turn it off!

853
00:31:22,614 --> 00:31:23,748
The blades are really strong.

854
00:31:24,883 --> 00:31:26,618
I guess it was too loud only for us.

855
00:31:26,684 --> 00:31:29,420
-I don't think he can hear well.
-Right?

856
00:31:29,487 --> 00:31:31,089
-What's that?
-He's pressing out the juice.

857
00:31:31,155 --> 00:31:33,524
He'll wring out the juice.

858
00:31:33,591 --> 00:31:35,727
-It must smell strong.
-Is he only using the juice?

859
00:31:35,793 --> 00:31:36,694
Yes.

860
00:31:36,761 --> 00:31:37,629
HE HEARD THIS ONE

861
00:31:37,695 --> 00:31:39,597
I think he's making green juice.

862
00:31:39,664 --> 00:31:40,899
-Just the extract.
-Yes.

863
00:31:40,965 --> 00:31:43,268
He's shaking it.

864
00:31:43,334 --> 00:31:45,336
Shake it.

865
00:31:45,637 --> 00:31:46,871
OH SO SILLY

866
00:31:46,938 --> 00:31:48,039
THE PERFUMER SMELLS IT!

867
00:31:48,106 --> 00:31:50,341
It smells good? Awesome.

868
00:31:50,408 --> 00:31:51,976
It smells like soap.

869
00:31:52,243 --> 00:31:53,978
THE TEACHER'S BUSY
BOTH PERFORMING AND COOKING

870
00:31:54,545 --> 00:31:56,648
-Eight minutes.
-Eight minutes?

871
00:31:56,714 --> 00:31:58,416
Frying powder? He's deep-frying again.

872
00:31:59,851 --> 00:32:02,420
THROW CHOPPED WATER PARSLEY
INTO THE BATTER!

873
00:32:03,054 --> 00:32:04,155
What's that?

874
00:32:04,222 --> 00:32:05,423
Oh, that's the <i>jeon</i>.

875
00:32:06,491 --> 00:32:08,960
-Water parsley <i>jeon</i>.
-You're right.

876
00:32:09,027 --> 00:32:10,028
The thickness is perfect.

877
00:32:10,094 --> 00:32:12,530
It looks perfect.

878
00:32:12,597 --> 00:32:14,799
<i>Jeon</i> made with too much batter

879
00:32:14,866 --> 00:32:16,901
fails to bring out
the ingredients' flavors.

880
00:32:16,968 --> 00:32:18,002
And the thickness looks perfect.

881
00:32:18,069 --> 00:32:19,537
I SEE

882
00:32:19,604 --> 00:32:21,339
-Just enough not to let it rip.
-Just enough.

883
00:32:21,406 --> 00:32:22,707
It only works as an adhesive.

884
00:32:22,774 --> 00:32:25,343
-He's spot on.
-To bring out the ingredient's flavor.

885
00:32:26,144 --> 00:32:27,378
It looks great.

886
00:32:28,146 --> 00:32:29,480
ADDING SOMETHING!

887
00:32:29,547 --> 00:32:31,749
-He added white wine and chili sauce.
-White wine?

888
00:32:31,816 --> 00:32:33,284
Also, orange vinegar.

889
00:32:34,285 --> 00:32:36,888
Orange vinegar.
I never figured out how to use that.

890
00:32:36,955 --> 00:32:39,090
What's that sauce for, Hyun-suk?

891
00:32:39,157 --> 00:32:40,558
Didn't I tell you?

892
00:32:41,626 --> 00:32:43,995
-That I'm the Perfumer Chef.
-Sure.

893
00:32:44,062 --> 00:32:46,664
-He asked what it's for.
-So what's it for?

894
00:32:46,731 --> 00:32:48,733
-He's not answering the question.
-No.

895
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:50,268
He's at that age.

896
00:32:51,135 --> 00:32:53,271
Long ago, it was tough
talking to my father

897
00:32:53,338 --> 00:32:55,573
because he kept changing the subject.

898
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:56,908
I'd ask, "Have you eaten, Father?"

899
00:32:56,975 --> 00:32:58,276
-He'd go, "Come home early!"
-"Come early!"

900
00:32:58,343 --> 00:32:59,277
MISCOMMUNICATION

901
00:32:59,344 --> 00:33:01,980
When I return from school,
he goes, "Why aren't you going to school?"

902
00:33:02,347 --> 00:33:04,449
ONLY LISTENS TO WHAT HE WANTS TO

903
00:33:05,416 --> 00:33:07,151
WHAT'S KIM POONG UP TO?

904
00:33:07,452 --> 00:33:09,087
BOILED HOG MAW OUT

905
00:33:09,153 --> 00:33:10,221
-It looks hot.
-Dang it.

906
00:33:10,288 --> 00:33:12,423
He finished boiling the hog maw.

907
00:33:12,490 --> 00:33:15,026
I hope he flips it smoothly.

908
00:33:15,827 --> 00:33:18,830
-All he has to do now is flip it.
-I hope it goes well.

909
00:33:18,896 --> 00:33:20,565
Don't let it turn into your pizza.

910
00:33:20,631 --> 00:33:22,734
-Five minutes left.
-Hey.

911
00:33:22,800 --> 00:33:24,902
-Sung-ju, please report from the kitchen.
-Already?

912
00:33:24,969 --> 00:33:27,472
-All right! Let me check.
-Hurry!

913
00:33:27,538 --> 00:33:28,473
Hey!

914
00:33:28,539 --> 00:33:30,742
-Something smelled good just now.
-Lemongrass.

915
00:33:30,808 --> 00:33:33,144
I already feel like
I could get drunk on the smell.

916
00:33:33,211 --> 00:33:35,947
There's a strong scent on this side.

917
00:33:36,514 --> 00:33:37,949
TIME TO FLIP!

918
00:33:38,016 --> 00:33:39,217
Will he flip it smoothly?

919
00:33:40,885 --> 00:33:41,753
LET'S GO!

920
00:33:43,321 --> 00:33:44,155
SUCCESS

921
00:33:44,956 --> 00:33:46,691
EVERYONE CELEBRATES

922
00:33:48,059 --> 00:33:49,527
A PERFECT FLIP

923
00:33:50,328 --> 00:33:51,729
-You did it.
-Yes!

924
00:33:51,796 --> 00:33:53,831
He was traumatized…

925
00:33:53,898 --> 00:33:56,734
-I overcame it.
-…after the round for Kim Gil-li.

926
00:33:57,301 --> 00:33:58,503
I'M PROUD OF YOU

927
00:33:58,569 --> 00:33:59,971
Poong.

928
00:34:00,038 --> 00:34:03,041
-You're adding hog maw into this?
-Yes, I am.

929
00:34:03,107 --> 00:34:05,109
You've never had it seasoned, have you?

930
00:34:05,176 --> 00:34:07,945
-No, never.
-It'll be delicious.

931
00:34:08,012 --> 00:34:11,215
-Let me try this one. The sauce.
-The sauce!

932
00:34:11,282 --> 00:34:13,384
-It must taste strong.
-That one.

933
00:34:13,951 --> 00:34:17,655
-Can he beat the show's champion?
-Salty, sour, and sweet.

934
00:34:17,722 --> 00:34:19,857
-Can he beat the show's champion?
-Salty, sour, and sweet.

935
00:34:20,491 --> 00:34:22,060
What's wrong?

936
00:34:22,794 --> 00:34:23,995
Is it too strong?

937
00:34:24,629 --> 00:34:26,431
HE SPAT IT OUT?

938
00:34:26,864 --> 00:34:28,866
WHAT ON EARTH IS IT LIKE?

939
00:34:29,434 --> 00:34:30,968
Is it too spicy?

940
00:34:31,035 --> 00:34:32,370
-It's spicy.
-It's too spicy.

941
00:34:32,437 --> 00:34:34,505
-It's spicy.
-It's too spicy!

942
00:34:34,572 --> 00:34:35,740
It's spicy!

943
00:34:35,807 --> 00:34:37,341
But Hyo-yeon will probably love it.

944
00:34:37,408 --> 00:34:39,377
-Do you think so?
-Yes.

945
00:34:39,444 --> 00:34:41,245
Sung-ju is good with spicy food too.

946
00:34:41,312 --> 00:34:42,547
-It's an emergency.
-But he…

947
00:34:42,613 --> 00:34:46,050
-It's spicy, and it's not my cup of tea.
-Is it fishy?

948
00:34:46,117 --> 00:34:48,052
The juice doesn't taste right to me.

949
00:34:48,119 --> 00:34:50,154
-It's probably the fish sauce.
-I used fish sauce.

950
00:34:50,221 --> 00:34:52,123
WILL HYO-YEON LIKE IT?

951
00:34:52,190 --> 00:34:53,591
Isn't it too spicy, though?

952
00:34:53,658 --> 00:34:54,826
-No, it's fine.
-Will it be fine?

953
00:34:54,892 --> 00:34:56,394
-I warned you, okay?
-Okay.

954
00:34:56,461 --> 00:34:57,762
Don't blame it on me later.

955
00:34:57,829 --> 00:34:59,764
POONG SEEMS SUSPICIOUSLY CONFIDENT

956
00:34:59,831 --> 00:35:00,798
Can you eat that?

957
00:35:00,865 --> 00:35:02,100
I'm good with spicy food.

958
00:35:02,166 --> 00:35:03,601
Can you flip this again?

959
00:35:03,668 --> 00:35:05,236
Did he rise above his trauma?

960
00:35:05,303 --> 00:35:06,671
-Poong!
-Wait, there's smoke.

961
00:35:06,737 --> 00:35:08,606
-You have to flip it.
-It's burning.

962
00:35:08,673 --> 00:35:10,007
Poong!

963
00:35:12,543 --> 00:35:13,511
Poong!

964
00:35:14,312 --> 00:35:15,580
ANOTHER DASHING SUCCESS

965
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:19,050
THE SCHOOL'S DOG MASTERED FLIPPING

966
00:35:19,117 --> 00:35:20,852
It's golden brown.

967
00:35:20,918 --> 00:35:22,353
-It looks perfect.
-It's amazing.

968
00:35:22,954 --> 00:35:25,223
WHILE EVERYONE HAS THEIR EYES ON POONG…

969
00:35:26,090 --> 00:35:27,558
WHAT'S HE DOING?

970
00:35:28,025 --> 00:35:30,027
THE GRANDPA PERFUMER MAKES PERFUME

971
00:35:30,495 --> 00:35:31,896
NO ONE SAW THAT, RIGHT?

972
00:35:32,163 --> 00:35:34,532
FIDGETING SECRETLY IN A CORNER…

973
00:35:34,599 --> 00:35:36,300
SPOTS HIM

974
00:35:36,367 --> 00:35:38,769
-What's Hyun-suk doing over there?
-Hyun-suk.

975
00:35:39,036 --> 00:35:40,638
HE THOUGHT HE COULD HIDE IT

976
00:35:40,705 --> 00:35:42,507
What's Hyun-suk doing over there?

977
00:35:42,573 --> 00:35:43,674
-Hyun-suk.
-No. 55.

978
00:35:43,741 --> 00:35:45,209
RAIDING THE SCENE

979
00:35:45,510 --> 00:35:47,445
HIDING HIS GOODS

980
00:35:47,512 --> 00:35:49,680
What? What's he doing? What did he do?

981
00:35:49,747 --> 00:35:51,415
He's writing something.

982
00:35:51,482 --> 00:35:52,984
-Write what?
-He wrote something.

983
00:35:53,551 --> 00:35:54,652
SHH!

984
00:35:54,719 --> 00:35:57,321
He hid his secret weapon back here.

985
00:35:57,388 --> 00:35:59,490
-He put sauce in that perfume bottle.
-Yes.

986
00:35:59,557 --> 00:36:01,726
-This is it.
-It's the mix.

987
00:36:01,792 --> 00:36:03,394
-Let me try this.
-It smelled so good.

988
00:36:03,461 --> 00:36:05,763
-I can smell it from here.
-The air's full of it.

989
00:36:05,830 --> 00:36:07,098
I don't think it's edible.

990
00:36:07,165 --> 00:36:08,900
He'll probably ask her to add a few drops.

991
00:36:08,966 --> 00:36:10,334
This is it.

992
00:36:10,401 --> 00:36:12,537
-Should I try this?
-Yes, please do.

993
00:36:12,603 --> 00:36:15,173
Is it designer perfume?
Or is it a knockoff?

994
00:36:15,239 --> 00:36:16,607
DESIGNER? KNOCKOFF?

995
00:36:16,674 --> 00:36:18,876
This is intricate.

996
00:36:18,943 --> 00:36:20,745
It's intricate. It smells like a perfume.

997
00:36:20,811 --> 00:36:22,313
But it's also delicious.

998
00:36:22,380 --> 00:36:23,981
-Hey.
-I don't hate it.

999
00:36:24,048 --> 00:36:26,083
It was a designer perfume.

1000
00:36:26,150 --> 00:36:28,953
And the scent lingers in your mouth.

1001
00:36:29,020 --> 00:36:30,488
THE PERFUMER CHEF LIVES UP TO HIS NICKNAME

1002
00:36:30,555 --> 00:36:31,789
It's fascinating.

1003
00:36:31,856 --> 00:36:34,125
PUTS ORANGE CHILI BUTTER SAUCE FIRST

1004
00:36:34,926 --> 00:36:36,427
That's Hyun-suk!

1005
00:36:36,494 --> 00:36:39,263
So this is what Hyun-suk does!

1006
00:36:39,330 --> 00:36:41,566
-You look like a grandpa.
-He's perfecting this!

1007
00:36:41,966 --> 00:36:43,868
THE GRANDPA'S DEVOTION!

1008
00:36:43,935 --> 00:36:47,038
He's a human measuring tool!

1009
00:36:47,104 --> 00:36:49,273
The soufflé looks perfect.

1010
00:36:49,740 --> 00:36:50,775
THE DOG BEGINS HIS CHASE

1011
00:36:51,209 --> 00:36:52,343
WATER PARSLEY JEON, OUT

1012
00:36:53,044 --> 00:36:54,278
It looks good.

1013
00:36:54,345 --> 00:36:55,880
Don't let your guard down, Poong.

1014
00:36:55,947 --> 00:36:57,782
Please don't. Hyun-suk's thing was nice.

1015
00:36:57,848 --> 00:36:59,617
That perfume-like substance was good.

1016
00:36:59,684 --> 00:37:02,019
That's the sauce.

1017
00:37:02,420 --> 00:37:04,155
HYUN-SUK FINISHES UP!

1018
00:37:04,722 --> 00:37:06,657
It was fascinating.

1019
00:37:06,724 --> 00:37:08,926
That's the steamed egg!

1020
00:37:08,993 --> 00:37:10,027
FLUFFY

1021
00:37:10,094 --> 00:37:11,095
It's pretty.

1022
00:37:11,162 --> 00:37:12,129
I'm dying to try it.

1023
00:37:13,731 --> 00:37:15,666
His apron came undone!

1024
00:37:16,834 --> 00:37:18,569
DROPS

1025
00:37:19,136 --> 00:37:21,172
TAKING OFF THE APRON

1026
00:37:21,239 --> 00:37:24,542
-He worked too hard and lost his apron!
-Look at him.

1027
00:37:24,609 --> 00:37:26,911
HOW UNSIGHTLY

1028
00:37:26,978 --> 00:37:28,579
That always happens to older people.

1029
00:37:28,646 --> 00:37:30,948
Older people always have
stuff falling off them.

1030
00:37:31,015 --> 00:37:32,683
-The apron came undone!
-No, it was dirty,

1031
00:37:32,750 --> 00:37:33,818
so I wanted to turn it over!

1032
00:37:34,952 --> 00:37:36,554
Hyun-suk turns his apron over.

1033
00:37:36,621 --> 00:37:38,322
It was so good.

1034
00:37:38,389 --> 00:37:41,592
Guys like him go to work
without wearing pants

1035
00:37:41,659 --> 00:37:43,327
with his suit jacket and necktie on.

1036
00:37:43,394 --> 00:37:45,329
-The yellow sauce.
-Let me try this.

1037
00:37:45,396 --> 00:37:48,199
He's done! He's already done!

1038
00:37:48,266 --> 00:37:49,367
He has a minute left.

1039
00:37:49,433 --> 00:37:51,569
I was going to try this
and give you my take.

1040
00:37:52,136 --> 00:37:53,237
WON'T COMMUNICATE

1041
00:37:53,304 --> 00:37:55,172
Forty seconds.

1042
00:37:55,239 --> 00:37:58,109
Poong has been traumatized
after that pizza incident.

1043
00:37:58,175 --> 00:37:59,610
What's this?

1044
00:37:59,677 --> 00:38:01,779
-Disposable gloves?
-That's right.

1045
00:38:01,846 --> 00:38:05,216
Poong's almost done too.
Twenty seconds. He's done!

1046
00:38:06,317 --> 00:38:08,686
-That looks good.
-Water parsley <i>jeon.</i>

1047
00:38:08,753 --> 00:38:09,987
DISHES WITH A BLAST OF AROMA

1048
00:38:10,054 --> 00:38:11,489
Are you serving that separately?

1049
00:38:11,555 --> 00:38:13,024
-In the last minute.
-The last minute.

1050
00:38:13,090 --> 00:38:15,192
-Those look good.
-They do.

1051
00:38:15,259 --> 00:38:16,227
THE DISHES ARE SERVED

1052
00:38:17,328 --> 00:38:19,597
-It's so pretty.
-My gosh.

1053
00:38:19,664 --> 00:38:21,766
-The visual…
-It's stunning.

1054
00:38:21,832 --> 00:38:23,834
Both dishes for Hyo-yeon are finished

1055
00:38:23,901 --> 00:38:26,937
to make her feel
Lost in the Scent, Holler.

1056
00:38:27,004 --> 00:38:29,307
I wasn't even out there cooking,

1057
00:38:29,373 --> 00:38:32,677
but I felt the heat even as I sat here.

1058
00:38:32,743 --> 00:38:36,047
First, please try the Perfumer Chef,
Chef Hyun-suk's dish.

1059
00:38:36,113 --> 00:38:39,717
-Senior.
-Senior No. 55.

1060
00:38:40,685 --> 00:38:43,287
FIRM YET FLUFFY SHRIMP SOUFFLÉ
WITH CHILI SAUCE

1061
00:38:44,155 --> 00:38:46,691
HIDDEN SECRET PERFUME

1062
00:38:47,425 --> 00:38:50,861
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S SENIOR NO. 55

1063
00:38:51,595 --> 00:38:53,964
-Chef Hyun-suk's here.
-He's approaching.

1064
00:38:54,031 --> 00:38:54,899
Hyun-suk's here.

1065
00:38:54,965 --> 00:38:57,368
Ma'am, would you like to smell this?

1066
00:38:59,670 --> 00:39:02,306
THE LETTERS HE WROTE DOWN

1067
00:39:02,807 --> 00:39:03,941
A SECRET WEAPON

1068
00:39:04,008 --> 00:39:05,443
HE HAD KEPT HIDDEN

1069
00:39:05,976 --> 00:39:07,244
CHOI'S NEW LINE, SENIOR NO. 55

1070
00:39:07,311 --> 00:39:09,013
It's like we're at a boutique.

1071
00:39:09,080 --> 00:39:10,715
Will she taste that?

1072
00:39:10,781 --> 00:39:11,716
No.

1073
00:39:12,483 --> 00:39:14,318
-Isn't it food?
-Are you serious?

1074
00:39:16,120 --> 00:39:18,155
HERE IT IS, MA'AM

1075
00:39:18,556 --> 00:39:20,725
THE HUMAN FRAGRANCE STRIP

1076
00:39:21,592 --> 00:39:22,927
OH MY GOD…

1077
00:39:23,260 --> 00:39:24,929
RECREATING THE BOUTIQUE EXPERIENCE

1078
00:39:25,262 --> 00:39:26,864
WILL SHE LIKE THE SMELL?

1079
00:39:26,931 --> 00:39:28,199
-It smells nice.
-It does.

1080
00:39:28,265 --> 00:39:30,501
And she can eat it too.

1081
00:39:30,568 --> 00:39:32,603
You're getting it on me.

1082
00:39:32,937 --> 00:39:35,840
SPRAYING IT EVERYWHERE

1083
00:39:35,906 --> 00:39:37,441
You can use it or eat it.

1084
00:39:37,508 --> 00:39:38,876
-That was too much.
-Wasn't it too much?

1085
00:39:38,943 --> 00:39:40,745
You can spray more if you wish.

1086
00:39:40,811 --> 00:39:42,413
Wow.

1087
00:39:42,480 --> 00:39:44,882
-You can use more.
-I can smell it from here.

1088
00:39:44,949 --> 00:39:46,550
It smells like lemongrass.

1089
00:39:46,617 --> 00:39:49,420
It smells really good.

1090
00:39:49,487 --> 00:39:51,689
-It smells like summer.
-Summer?

1091
00:39:51,756 --> 00:39:53,491
-It does.
-That refreshing smell.

1092
00:39:53,557 --> 00:39:55,893
But what will it taste like?

1093
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:58,396
You'll find shrimp and okra inside,

1094
00:39:58,462 --> 00:40:00,231
so cut it into big pieces and enjoy it.

1095
00:40:00,498 --> 00:40:02,099
CLOSE-UP EXAMINATION

1096
00:40:02,166 --> 00:40:04,468
I see large pieces of shrimp inside.

1097
00:40:05,002 --> 00:40:06,904
ENJOYING THE SCENT FIRST

1098
00:40:08,038 --> 00:40:10,141
-Does it smell strong?
-It looks soft.

1099
00:40:13,477 --> 00:40:14,912
SMILING

1100
00:40:14,979 --> 00:40:17,081
WHAT DOES THAT SMILE MEAN?

1101
00:40:17,148 --> 00:40:18,616
<i>Holler</i>

1102
00:40:18,682 --> 00:40:20,451
GETTING LOST JUST BY WATCHING HER

1103
00:40:20,518 --> 00:40:22,853
First off, it's absolutely delicious.

1104
00:40:23,087 --> 00:40:24,088
RELIEVED

1105
00:40:24,155 --> 00:40:26,190
The okra pieces aren't just slimy,

1106
00:40:26,257 --> 00:40:28,225
but also has a crunchy texture,

1107
00:40:28,292 --> 00:40:30,461
and the shrimp pieces pop in my mouth.

1108
00:40:30,528 --> 00:40:32,229
The balance is really nice.

1109
00:40:32,296 --> 00:40:33,831
A PERFECT HARMONY OF TEXTURE

1110
00:40:34,131 --> 00:40:35,633
ANOTHER BIG BITE

1111
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:37,168
MMM

1112
00:40:37,234 --> 00:40:38,869
You look so happy.

1113
00:40:38,936 --> 00:40:40,070
It's really good.

1114
00:40:40,137 --> 00:40:42,006
HAPPINESS METER GOING UP

1115
00:40:42,072 --> 00:40:44,408
Can you spray the perfume on that?

1116
00:40:44,475 --> 00:40:46,444
-Should I?
-Yes, that No. 55.

1117
00:40:46,510 --> 00:40:50,214
The way the second five
is squished on the edge

1118
00:40:50,281 --> 00:40:51,182
is too funny.

1119
00:40:51,749 --> 00:40:53,951
The spray works nicely.

1120
00:40:54,018 --> 00:40:55,186
What's the smell like?

1121
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:57,988
-Can you smell it?
-Can you?

1122
00:40:58,055 --> 00:41:01,325
-I can probably drench this with it.
-You can do that.

1123
00:41:01,392 --> 00:41:04,261
I tried the liquid as is,

1124
00:41:04,328 --> 00:41:07,798
-and the aroma lingered in my mouth.
-I can smell it. It's subtle.

1125
00:41:07,865 --> 00:41:08,966
It really is like a perfume.

1126
00:41:10,434 --> 00:41:11,502
This is it.

1127
00:41:11,569 --> 00:41:12,636
-"This is it"?
-I should have

1128
00:41:12,703 --> 00:41:15,239
-drenched the egg with the spray…
-Do you need it?

1129
00:41:15,306 --> 00:41:17,074
…to make me get drunk on the scent.

1130
00:41:17,741 --> 00:41:19,109
That was so creative.

1131
00:41:19,176 --> 00:41:21,245
I was first hit with lemongrass,

1132
00:41:21,312 --> 00:41:24,882
then the shrimp and other ingredients
slowly spread in the mouth.

1133
00:41:24,949 --> 00:41:26,150
I see.

1134
00:41:26,217 --> 00:41:27,985
It almost feels Chinese,

1135
00:41:28,052 --> 00:41:29,286
but then it's Western,

1136
00:41:29,353 --> 00:41:31,255
and I can also taste Southeast Asian food.

1137
00:41:31,322 --> 00:41:32,456
It's crazy and chaotic.

1138
00:41:32,523 --> 00:41:34,425
-Crazy and chaotic?
-Crazy and chaotic?

1139
00:41:34,492 --> 00:41:35,926
-It's so creative.
-This is a must

1140
00:41:35,993 --> 00:41:39,196
to maximize the flavor of this dish.

1141
00:41:39,263 --> 00:41:40,764
The more, the better.

1142
00:41:41,398 --> 00:41:44,001
-You can even pour it on top.
-Even pour it on top.

1143
00:41:44,068 --> 00:41:47,905
And next, try Webtoon Artist Poong's
Hyun-suk, Way to Go.

1144
00:41:48,439 --> 00:41:51,408
SPICY DIP
WITH A GENEROUS AMOUNT OF HOG MAW

1145
00:41:52,676 --> 00:41:56,080
AROMATIC AND CRUNCHY WATER PARSLEY JEON

1146
00:41:57,181 --> 00:42:00,351
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S
HYUN-SUK, WAY TO GO

1147
00:42:00,951 --> 00:42:03,087
-My gosh.
-He worked hard on the sauce.

1148
00:42:03,153 --> 00:42:05,589
-You served her disposable gloves.
-Yes.

1149
00:42:05,656 --> 00:42:06,957
First, put the gloves on.

1150
00:42:07,024 --> 00:42:08,692
You'll see that
I cut the jeon in quarters.

1151
00:42:08,759 --> 00:42:12,530
Pick up a piece,
then top it with a nice amount of dip

1152
00:42:12,596 --> 00:42:13,864
and eat it like pizza.

1153
00:42:13,931 --> 00:42:16,667
-He's obsessed with the idea of pizza.
-He's obsessed.

1154
00:42:17,902 --> 00:42:19,403
Because Gil-li's pizza was ruined.

1155
00:42:19,904 --> 00:42:21,672
MR. OBSESSING WITH PIZZA

1156
00:42:21,739 --> 00:42:23,941
I really love <i>jeon</i>.

1157
00:42:24,008 --> 00:42:26,944
I like to eat it on special occasions,

1158
00:42:27,011 --> 00:42:30,681
-and this water parsley <i>jeon</i> hits home.
-Really?

1159
00:42:30,748 --> 00:42:33,784
Try a bite of the hog maw first
with your chopsticks.

1160
00:42:33,851 --> 00:42:38,122
-It looks like a Southeast Asian sauce.
-Yes.

1161
00:42:38,188 --> 00:42:40,324
It feels like you'll need
a tuk-tuk to go home later.

1162
00:42:41,325 --> 00:42:42,660
Now, the hog maw.

1163
00:42:42,726 --> 00:42:45,362
Was it Thai chili? That was spicy.

1164
00:42:45,429 --> 00:42:46,297
So?

1165
00:42:46,897 --> 00:42:47,965
Mmm.

1166
00:42:48,032 --> 00:42:50,701
-I just had a piece of hog maw.
-Yes.

1167
00:42:50,768 --> 00:42:53,971
But it's been boiled
much better than how I usually eat it,

1168
00:42:54,038 --> 00:42:56,307
-so it's even more tender.
-I see.

1169
00:42:56,373 --> 00:42:57,608
It tastes classy.

1170
00:42:59,043 --> 00:43:00,544
-Let me try the sauce.
-The sauce.

1171
00:43:01,245 --> 00:43:02,246
I'm curious.

1172
00:43:04,248 --> 00:43:05,115
Isn't it spicy?

1173
00:43:05,182 --> 00:43:06,517
No, not at all.

1174
00:43:06,584 --> 00:43:08,419
-Are you serious?
-I am.

1175
00:43:08,485 --> 00:43:09,753
But this smell.

1176
00:43:09,820 --> 00:43:11,322
I think it's a hit or miss.

1177
00:43:11,388 --> 00:43:12,890
It must be

1178
00:43:12,957 --> 00:43:14,858
because he added sambal.

1179
00:43:14,925 --> 00:43:17,294
-Yes.
-It feels like

1180
00:43:17,361 --> 00:43:18,996
it's been preserved for ten months.

1181
00:43:21,165 --> 00:43:22,666
I also added fish sauce.

1182
00:43:22,733 --> 00:43:25,235
-That must be it.
-Something smelled musty.

1183
00:43:25,302 --> 00:43:28,205
Fish sauce is a must
for Southeast Asian cuisine.

1184
00:43:28,272 --> 00:43:30,240
I would've loved it even more

1185
00:43:30,307 --> 00:43:32,042
with a dash of vinegar.

1186
00:43:33,510 --> 00:43:34,745
Right now, it's really good,

1187
00:43:34,812 --> 00:43:38,148
but I'm mostly captivated
by the musty smell.

1188
00:43:38,215 --> 00:43:39,650
-Fish Sauce No. 5 is strong.
-Captivated.

1189
00:43:39,717 --> 00:43:42,386
-Fish Sauce No. 5?
-Fish Sauce No. 5?

1190
00:43:43,387 --> 00:43:44,455
RETRYING FISH SAUCE NO. 5

1191
00:43:44,521 --> 00:43:47,024
She continues to try the sauce
without the <i>jeon</i>.

1192
00:43:47,091 --> 00:43:48,626
It's spicy.

1193
00:43:48,692 --> 00:43:50,361
-See? It is!
-You'll start to feel it.

1194
00:43:50,427 --> 00:43:51,929
-Yes.
-It must hit you later.

1195
00:43:51,996 --> 00:43:55,065
-She's a bit flustered.
-It was shocking for me.

1196
00:43:55,132 --> 00:43:57,434
-But there's <i>jeon</i>. Yes.
-The sauce is spicy on its own,

1197
00:43:57,501 --> 00:43:58,702
but she'll have it with <i>jeon</i>.

1198
00:43:58,769 --> 00:44:01,205
Let me try just the <i>jeon</i>.

1199
00:44:01,271 --> 00:44:02,773
-Just the water parsley <i>jeon</i>.
-Sure.

1200
00:44:02,840 --> 00:44:03,774
It looks good.

1201
00:44:04,541 --> 00:44:06,210
CRUNCH

1202
00:44:06,276 --> 00:44:07,711
She likes water parsley <i>jeon</i>.

1203
00:44:09,947 --> 00:44:11,115
Mmm.

1204
00:44:11,181 --> 00:44:12,449
-It must be good.
-It has to be.

1205
00:44:12,516 --> 00:44:14,385
I can already tell by the sound.

1206
00:44:14,451 --> 00:44:16,053
Isn't it too much water parsley?

1207
00:44:16,120 --> 00:44:18,022
I like dishes that have a strong presence.

1208
00:44:19,256 --> 00:44:20,290
"It's me, water parsley!"

1209
00:44:20,357 --> 00:44:22,026
She likes it.

1210
00:44:22,092 --> 00:44:23,994
It might be different
when she tries it together.

1211
00:44:24,061 --> 00:44:25,629
Please avoid the red stuff.

1212
00:44:26,497 --> 00:44:28,599
I've never had sauce like this before.

1213
00:44:28,666 --> 00:44:29,933
She's never had anything like it.

1214
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:31,802
-He put lots of work into it.
-Yes.

1215
00:44:31,869 --> 00:44:32,703
YUM

1216
00:44:32,770 --> 00:44:35,105
She already likes water parsley <i>jeon</i>, so…

1217
00:44:35,172 --> 00:44:36,373
What's it like?

1218
00:44:36,440 --> 00:44:38,509
I wonder what it's like.

1219
00:44:38,575 --> 00:44:40,144
The smell of water parsley

1220
00:44:40,210 --> 00:44:41,879
covers that musty smell.

1221
00:44:43,080 --> 00:44:45,249
These work better
when I eat them together.

1222
00:44:45,315 --> 00:44:47,017
TOGETHER, THE DISH HAS A GOOD BALANCE

1223
00:44:47,084 --> 00:44:49,553
I want to try… May I borrow this?

1224
00:44:49,620 --> 00:44:50,854
SENIOR NO. 55?

1225
00:44:50,921 --> 00:44:53,624
Chef Hyun-suk's Senior No. 55.

1226
00:44:53,957 --> 00:44:57,561
A GENEROUS AMOUNT

1227
00:44:57,628 --> 00:45:01,365
Senior No. 55 meets Fish Sauce No. 5.

1228
00:45:01,432 --> 00:45:04,768
I wonder what water parsley
and lemongrass will taste like.

1229
00:45:05,402 --> 00:45:09,106
-No one has tried that before.
-She tries mixing the two.

1230
00:45:09,173 --> 00:45:10,674
-Mmm.
-Mmm.

1231
00:45:10,741 --> 00:45:12,876
HAS SHE FOUND A DELICIOUS NEW COMBINATION?

1232
00:45:13,343 --> 00:45:14,244
It's better separately.

1233
00:45:15,546 --> 00:45:18,782
-No, Hyun-suk and Poong can't mix.
-It's impossible.

1234
00:45:18,849 --> 00:45:21,351
-I thought so.
-They're two distinct people.

1235
00:45:22,052 --> 00:45:23,454
They're both self-assertive.

1236
00:45:23,520 --> 00:45:26,390
-Both are self-assertive.
-Just like those two.

1237
00:45:26,457 --> 00:45:29,593
Then Tiffany, please try the dishes too.

1238
00:45:29,660 --> 00:45:30,527
Thank you.

1239
00:45:30,594 --> 00:45:33,597
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S SENIOR NO. 55

1240
00:45:33,664 --> 00:45:35,499
It's the kind of scent that I like.

1241
00:45:35,566 --> 00:45:37,201
-Doesn't it smell good?
-Yes.

1242
00:45:37,267 --> 00:45:40,771
She might like this one.

1243
00:45:41,805 --> 00:45:43,006
Mmm.

1244
00:45:43,941 --> 00:45:44,975
What do you think?

1245
00:45:46,043 --> 00:45:48,011
I'm hit with a blast of aroma.

1246
00:45:48,078 --> 00:45:49,279
YUM

1247
00:45:50,047 --> 00:45:50,981
-Mmm.
-It's good.

1248
00:45:51,048 --> 00:45:52,282
IT'S GOOD

1249
00:45:52,349 --> 00:45:54,318
It's in a lump,

1250
00:45:54,384 --> 00:45:57,321
but when you eat it,
you can taste every ingredient inside.

1251
00:45:58,689 --> 00:46:00,023
I like it.

1252
00:46:00,090 --> 00:46:01,892
She sprays a lot of sauce.

1253
00:46:01,959 --> 00:46:03,427
EVEN TIFFANY IS LOST IN SENIOR NO. 55

1254
00:46:03,494 --> 00:46:05,963
Yes, you should spray lots of sauce.

1255
00:46:06,029 --> 00:46:06,864
Mmm.

1256
00:46:06,930 --> 00:46:09,466
-It's even better right after spraying it.
-Is it?

1257
00:46:09,933 --> 00:46:11,235
EDDIE ADDS SOME MORE AROMA

1258
00:46:11,301 --> 00:46:12,936
Chef Eddie tries some too.

1259
00:46:13,003 --> 00:46:15,672
STRAIGHT INTO THE MOUTH

1260
00:46:15,739 --> 00:46:18,041
-What do you think?
-Mmm.

1261
00:46:18,108 --> 00:46:21,411
Next, Webtoon Artist Kim Poong's dish,
Hyun-suk, Way to Go.

1262
00:46:21,478 --> 00:46:24,681
I wonder what the chefs will say.

1263
00:46:24,748 --> 00:46:28,185
Hyo-yeon said it was really delicious.

1264
00:46:28,252 --> 00:46:29,853
It's made with hog maw.

1265
00:46:29,920 --> 00:46:33,190
I really love water parsley <i>jeon.</i>

1266
00:46:33,757 --> 00:46:35,826
Tiffany takes a bite too.

1267
00:46:35,893 --> 00:46:36,760
TIFFANY TAKES A BIG BITE

1268
00:46:37,261 --> 00:46:39,763
The smell of water parsley
spreads toward the end.

1269
00:46:39,830 --> 00:46:41,598
The water parsley <i>jeon </i>is so good.

1270
00:46:41,665 --> 00:46:42,499
It's good.

1271
00:46:43,734 --> 00:46:46,203
-Tiffany tries the hog maw!
-She is?

1272
00:46:46,270 --> 00:46:47,404
Doesn't it feel like squid?

1273
00:46:48,205 --> 00:46:49,239
Half-dried squid.

1274
00:46:49,306 --> 00:46:50,741
It's an actual "inside" of an animal.

1275
00:46:50,808 --> 00:46:52,209
WILL SHE LIKE IT?

1276
00:46:55,212 --> 00:46:56,113
I respect your taste.

1277
00:46:58,382 --> 00:46:59,850
"I respect your taste."

1278
00:46:59,917 --> 00:47:03,086
I RESPECT THAT SHE LIKES IT

1279
00:47:05,856 --> 00:47:07,090
Why do you keep chugging water?

1280
00:47:07,157 --> 00:47:08,826
-It's so spicy.
-Right.

1281
00:47:09,660 --> 00:47:11,728
EDDIE CAN'T TAKE THE SPICINESS EITHER

1282
00:47:11,795 --> 00:47:15,732
It's spicy. Isn't it spicy, Edward? It is.

1283
00:47:15,999 --> 00:47:17,868
THE SPICINESS CREEPS UP

1284
00:47:18,869 --> 00:47:19,837
Wow.

1285
00:47:21,905 --> 00:47:23,473
I TOLD YOU I'D GIVE YOU A NOOGIE!

1286
00:47:23,540 --> 00:47:24,741
It suddenly hits you.

1287
00:47:24,808 --> 00:47:27,911
This isn't just a kick.
It's like a roundhouse kick.

1288
00:47:27,978 --> 00:47:30,514
-Not just a kick, but a roundhouse kick?
-A roundhouse kick?

1289
00:47:30,581 --> 00:47:33,684
When I saw what the <i>jeon </i>looked like,

1290
00:47:33,750 --> 00:47:35,719
I thought I was visiting
a Korean folk village.

1291
00:47:35,786 --> 00:47:39,089
But then I was hit with the scent
of a luxury hotel in Southeast Asia.

1292
00:47:39,156 --> 00:47:41,525
-Bangkok.
-It suddenly hit me.

1293
00:47:41,592 --> 00:47:42,893
Southeast…

1294
00:47:42,960 --> 00:47:43,994
Southeast…

1295
00:47:45,195 --> 00:47:46,163
SPEECHLESS

1296
00:47:46,230 --> 00:47:47,364
"You got that from this?"

1297
00:47:47,431 --> 00:47:48,932
From this one?

1298
00:47:49,199 --> 00:47:50,367
THE FINAL SHOT

1299
00:47:51,468 --> 00:47:52,536
STANDS FIRM ON "THIS"

1300
00:47:52,603 --> 00:47:54,338
-I respect that.
-She respects it.

1301
00:47:54,404 --> 00:47:55,372
I respect your opinion.

1302
00:47:55,439 --> 00:47:58,709
-And now, it's Hyo-yeon's turn to choose.
-This is hard.

1303
00:47:58,775 --> 00:48:00,811
<i>Press one for Hyun-suk</i>

1304
00:48:00,878 --> 00:48:03,180
<i>and two for Poong.</i>

1305
00:48:03,247 --> 00:48:05,649
Make your decision and press the button!

1306
00:48:06,950 --> 00:48:09,553
Which scent did she like better?

1307
00:48:09,620 --> 00:48:12,389
-I made my choice.
-Did you push it?

1308
00:48:12,456 --> 00:48:14,892
Who did she choose?

1309
00:48:14,958 --> 00:48:16,860
Let's find out the winner.

1310
00:48:16,927 --> 00:48:20,898
This is their first cook-off in 2026.

1311
00:48:20,964 --> 00:48:22,966
Poong has four stars,
and Hyun-suk has two.

1312
00:48:23,033 --> 00:48:25,302
Will Hyun-suk recover his reputation?

1313
00:48:25,369 --> 00:48:27,404
Or will Poong take the lead yet again?

1314
00:48:27,471 --> 00:48:29,206
Which scent

1315
00:48:29,273 --> 00:48:31,742
did Hyo-yeon feel more lost in?

1316
00:48:31,808 --> 00:48:34,244
Who did she choose?

1317
00:48:34,311 --> 00:48:36,780
Who did she choose?

1318
00:48:37,014 --> 00:48:38,282
CHOI HYUN-SUK WINS

1319
00:48:38,348 --> 00:48:39,283
It was Hyun-suk.

1320
00:48:39,349 --> 00:48:41,618
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S SENIOR NO. 55 WINS

1321
00:48:41,685 --> 00:48:44,955
She chose Chef Hyun-suk's dish.

1322
00:48:47,391 --> 00:48:48,959
A HUG

1323
00:48:49,026 --> 00:48:51,194
-He looks thrilled.
-He does.

1324
00:48:51,261 --> 00:48:54,598
First of all,
Chef Poong's water parsley <i>jeon</i>

1325
00:48:54,665 --> 00:48:57,000
was right up my alley,

1326
00:48:57,067 --> 00:48:59,903
but instead of the flavor
of Southeast Asian cuisine,

1327
00:48:59,970 --> 00:49:02,105
it tasted mostly like fish sauce.

1328
00:49:02,172 --> 00:49:03,507
-It was too strong.
-However,

1329
00:49:03,573 --> 00:49:06,877
I had always wondered
what I should make with hog maw,

1330
00:49:06,944 --> 00:49:09,112
and I appreciated this idea.

1331
00:49:09,179 --> 00:49:12,149
Also, Chef Hyun-suk's dish.

1332
00:49:13,884 --> 00:49:15,886
It was so harmonious in my mouth.

1333
00:49:15,953 --> 00:49:19,222
The moment I sprayed Senior No. 55 on it,

1334
00:49:19,289 --> 00:49:21,625
I immediately thought of a forest.

1335
00:49:21,692 --> 00:49:24,294
-You could feel the phytoncide.
-Also,

1336
00:49:24,361 --> 00:49:26,596
it was so romantic of him
to put it in a perfume bottle.

1337
00:49:26,663 --> 00:49:30,267
I also liked the way you presented it.

1338
00:49:30,334 --> 00:49:31,835
It was great.

1339
00:49:31,902 --> 00:49:34,304
-What was your dish called again?
-What was it?

1340
00:49:37,941 --> 00:49:40,711
-Chef Hyun-suk.
-Please put a star on him!

1341
00:49:40,777 --> 00:49:43,413
CONGRATULATIONS, SENIOR

1342
00:49:43,480 --> 00:49:46,416
Chef Hyun-suk gets his third star.

1343
00:49:46,483 --> 00:49:50,120
He's making his way up the ranks!

1344
00:49:50,187 --> 00:49:54,291
<i>The second round cook-off</i>
<i>with ingredients from Hyo-yeon's fridge.</i>

1345
00:49:54,358 --> 00:49:56,560
The Hyo-yeon of <i>Chef & My Fridge,</i>
Chef Jung Ho-young.

1346
00:49:56,626 --> 00:49:58,428
HO-YEON, NOT HYO-YEON

1347
00:49:58,495 --> 00:50:02,632
The Fedor Emelianenko of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,
Chef Yoon Nam-no.

1348
00:50:02,966 --> 00:50:05,102
DRUNK ON BEER, HOLLER
YOON NAM-NO VS. JUNG HO-YOUNG

1349
00:50:05,168 --> 00:50:07,004
Chef Nam-no

1350
00:50:07,070 --> 00:50:09,606
jumped into the beer snack round

1351
00:50:10,674 --> 00:50:12,676
with a lot of confidence.

1352
00:50:12,743 --> 00:50:14,444
But when Park Myung-soo was here,

1353
00:50:14,511 --> 00:50:16,613
you made a wine snack

1354
00:50:16,680 --> 00:50:18,515
instead of a beer snack as he asked.

1355
00:50:18,582 --> 00:50:20,250
Chef Nam-no's dish was classy.

1356
00:50:20,317 --> 00:50:22,419
HE DIDN'T GET THE TOPIC
AND MADE A WINE SNACK INSTEAD

1357
00:50:22,486 --> 00:50:25,188
And you had lost to Poong back then.

1358
00:50:25,255 --> 00:50:26,189
-I did.
-Do you remember?

1359
00:50:26,256 --> 00:50:28,658
I didn't understand the order back then,

1360
00:50:28,725 --> 00:50:30,160
but today, I did.

1361
00:50:30,227 --> 00:50:33,030
So I'll make a perfect beer snack,

1362
00:50:33,096 --> 00:50:34,898
-a soup dish… Wait, no.
-What?

1363
00:50:34,965 --> 00:50:37,000
-A beer snack?
-No, a perfect beer snack.

1364
00:50:37,067 --> 00:50:39,403
-Soups are usually for soju.
-A soup dish?

1365
00:50:39,469 --> 00:50:41,505
-What's he saying?
-He's making a random bar snack.

1366
00:50:41,571 --> 00:50:42,773
Wake up, man!

1367
00:50:42,839 --> 00:50:44,841
He doesn't know what the test is on.

1368
00:50:44,908 --> 00:50:46,176
I figured out what she likes,

1369
00:50:46,243 --> 00:50:48,612
so I'll make a savory dish

1370
00:50:48,678 --> 00:50:50,514
that'll go perfectly with beer.

1371
00:50:50,580 --> 00:50:52,049
Ho-young, do you drink beer often?

1372
00:50:52,115 --> 00:50:54,451
I've been drinking beer
for at least ten more years

1373
00:50:54,518 --> 00:50:56,053
than Nam-no has.

1374
00:50:56,853 --> 00:50:58,989
-Yes, even if they had the same amount.
-I know I can do this.

1375
00:50:59,056 --> 00:51:00,857
I may be much younger,

1376
00:51:00,924 --> 00:51:03,660
but I'm second to none when it comes
to the amount of food consumed.

1377
00:51:03,727 --> 00:51:05,862
And whenever I drink beer,

1378
00:51:05,929 --> 00:51:08,432
-I start at about 5 L.
-What? 5 L?

1379
00:51:08,498 --> 00:51:09,332
-Five liters?
-Five liters?

1380
00:51:09,399 --> 00:51:12,169
-Did you say 5 L?
-So ten 500 cc glasses.

1381
00:51:12,235 --> 00:51:13,837
It's like a jerry can full of beer.

1382
00:51:13,904 --> 00:51:15,672
You shouldn't even drink that much water.

1383
00:51:15,739 --> 00:51:17,340
So he stuffs himself without thinking.

1384
00:51:18,842 --> 00:51:20,177
"Without thinking"?

1385
00:51:20,243 --> 00:51:21,645
Again, for this round,

1386
00:51:21,711 --> 00:51:25,315
Chef Sung-jun will accompany
Jung-hwan for the interim check.

1387
00:51:25,382 --> 00:51:27,350
He could've done better
in the last episode.

1388
00:51:27,417 --> 00:51:29,553
HE INDIFFERENTLY SAID, "IT'S A PARTY"

1389
00:51:29,619 --> 00:51:30,454
Make it sound exciting.

1390
00:51:30,520 --> 00:51:32,656
HARSH ON THE YOUNGEST MEMBER

1391
00:51:32,722 --> 00:51:34,925
TEARY-EYED

1392
00:51:34,991 --> 00:51:36,993
Do you remember? Even Chef Jong-won

1393
00:51:37,060 --> 00:51:39,830
let go of himself and went,
"He's the champion!"

1394
00:51:39,896 --> 00:51:41,765
-Yes.
-"The champion!"

1395
00:51:41,832 --> 00:51:43,500
I fell ill for a week after doing that.

1396
00:51:44,301 --> 00:51:46,803
-He used up all his energy.
-You tried to make it easy.

1397
00:51:46,870 --> 00:51:48,205
He shouldn't do that.

1398
00:51:48,271 --> 00:51:50,440
-Try harder, Sung-jun.
-I'll do my best.

1399
00:51:51,274 --> 00:51:53,310
CHEF HO-YOUNG'S INGREDIENTS:
CHINESE YAM, NATTO, OKRA, HOG MAW

1400
00:51:53,376 --> 00:51:55,445
CILANTRO, PERILLA POWDER, THAI CHILI,
SAMBAL, TSUYU, LEMON JUICE

1401
00:51:55,512 --> 00:51:58,548
And now, let's find out
what the chefs are making today.

1402
00:51:58,615 --> 00:52:01,017
What are you making, Chef Ho-young?

1403
00:52:01,084 --> 00:52:03,019
I'm going to make a Chinese yam dish.

1404
00:52:03,086 --> 00:52:06,723
First, she said
she liked the gooey texture,

1405
00:52:06,790 --> 00:52:10,594
so I'll use yam, okra, and natto
to whip up a noodle dish.

1406
00:52:10,660 --> 00:52:12,395
-Wow.
-For the second dish,

1407
00:52:12,462 --> 00:52:15,932
I plan to make
crispy deep-fried Chinese yam,

1408
00:52:15,999 --> 00:52:18,668
and I'll also deep-fry some hog maw.

1409
00:52:18,735 --> 00:52:20,103
That sounds good.

1410
00:52:20,170 --> 00:52:24,508
I'll also mix perilla powder and mayo
to make perilla mayo.

1411
00:52:24,574 --> 00:52:26,276
It'll save you
from the peril of a hangover.

1412
00:52:26,343 --> 00:52:28,979
-What?
-The "peril" of a hangover.

1413
00:52:29,813 --> 00:52:31,948
CHEF NAM-NO'S INGREDIENTS:
CHICKEN GIZZARD, HOG MAW, SMOKED CHICKEN

1414
00:52:32,015 --> 00:52:34,317
ABAI SUNDAE, BEEF TENDERLOIN, STRIP LOIN,
QUAIL EGG JANG-JORIM, AND MORE

1415
00:52:34,384 --> 00:52:36,620
Nam-no must be feeling some pressure.

1416
00:52:36,686 --> 00:52:38,522
He's stretching his back.

1417
00:52:38,588 --> 00:52:41,525
-He's warming up.
-Huh? Are you going to do something?

1418
00:52:41,591 --> 00:52:42,759
HAHAHAHAHA

1419
00:52:42,826 --> 00:52:44,828
What are you making, Nam-no?

1420
00:52:44,895 --> 00:52:46,196
Will he do something big?

1421
00:52:46,263 --> 00:52:47,430
Meatball King?

1422
00:52:47,497 --> 00:52:49,032
-It's Meatball King.
-Meatball King.

1423
00:52:51,568 --> 00:52:52,736
All right.

1424
00:52:52,802 --> 00:52:55,372
Anyway, that was the dance.
And you're making Meatball King?

1425
00:52:55,438 --> 00:52:57,340
What's the dish like?

1426
00:52:57,407 --> 00:52:59,109
I'll make
a British deep-fried meatball dish

1427
00:52:59,176 --> 00:53:00,877
called a Scotch egg.

1428
00:53:00,944 --> 00:53:02,345
-Scotch egg.
-Scotch egg?

1429
00:53:02,412 --> 00:53:04,147
I'll use Hyo-yeon's favorite ingredients,

1430
00:53:04,214 --> 00:53:07,317
hog maw, chicken gizzard,
and smoked chicken.

1431
00:53:07,384 --> 00:53:09,986
I'll use these three to make soup curry.

1432
00:53:10,053 --> 00:53:11,922
SOUP CURRY MADE OF "INSIDES"

1433
00:53:11,988 --> 00:53:13,356
With hog maw?

1434
00:53:13,423 --> 00:53:16,593
Curry goes very well with offal.

1435
00:53:16,660 --> 00:53:18,228
CONFIDENT THAT THEY'LL GO WELL!

1436
00:53:18,628 --> 00:53:20,697
LOOKING FORWARD TO IT

1437
00:53:20,764 --> 00:53:23,166
I'm Genie for Chinese Yam
versus Meatball King…

1438
00:53:23,233 --> 00:53:24,267
WHERE'S HE GOING?

1439
00:53:24,334 --> 00:53:26,269
Let us begin the round now.

1440
00:53:26,336 --> 00:53:27,370
Good luck!

1441
00:53:27,437 --> 00:53:28,572
Good luck.

1442
00:53:28,638 --> 00:53:31,308
Why didn't you put the apron on before?

1443
00:53:31,374 --> 00:53:33,310
He didn't put it on to dance.

1444
00:53:33,376 --> 00:53:35,212
Because it'll pop.

1445
00:53:35,278 --> 00:53:36,313
LOL

1446
00:53:36,379 --> 00:53:38,181
And he can't do it alone.

1447
00:53:39,382 --> 00:53:41,084
-Pull it down a little.
-Pull it down.

1448
00:53:41,151 --> 00:53:43,053
He can't even wear the apron by himself?

1449
00:53:43,119 --> 00:53:44,588
Isn't it better not to wear one?

1450
00:53:44,654 --> 00:53:46,590
He's not cut out to work as a chef.

1451
00:53:46,656 --> 00:53:47,557
-Is that armor?
-Right?

1452
00:53:47,824 --> 00:53:49,392
1 COMBO
CALLING IT ARMOR

1453
00:53:49,459 --> 00:53:52,028
2 COMBO
CALLING IT A BULLETPROOF VEST

1454
00:53:52,095 --> 00:53:53,363
-A bulletproof vest?
-It's like…

1455
00:53:53,930 --> 00:53:55,565
I think it's choking him.

1456
00:53:55,632 --> 00:53:57,567
-All right.
-Yes, let's go.

1457
00:53:57,634 --> 00:54:00,570
He received good energy from Eun-yeong

1458
00:54:00,637 --> 00:54:03,873
to become the show's king,
Chef Yoon Nam-no.

1459
00:54:03,940 --> 00:54:06,543
But this man thinks
Nam-no should know his place,

1460
00:54:06,610 --> 00:54:09,045
Chef Jung Ho-young.

1461
00:54:09,579 --> 00:54:11,715
Which one of them
will capture Hyo-yeon's heart?

1462
00:54:11,781 --> 00:54:15,118
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1463
00:54:16,753 --> 00:54:17,621
GODFATHER!

1464
00:54:18,588 --> 00:54:20,423
You're making beer snacks.

1465
00:54:20,490 --> 00:54:22,559
Bar snacks that'll go well with beer.

1466
00:54:22,626 --> 00:54:23,793
Gizzard.

1467
00:54:23,860 --> 00:54:26,029
Nam-no goes straight for gizzards.

1468
00:54:26,096 --> 00:54:27,864
-<i>Sundae</i>.
-He's using <i>sundae </i>too.

1469
00:54:27,931 --> 00:54:30,033
-<i>Abai sundae</i>.
-Hamgyeong-do style <i>sundae</i>.

1470
00:54:30,100 --> 00:54:31,935
HOG MAW

1471
00:54:32,435 --> 00:54:33,303
STARTING WITH YAM

1472
00:54:33,370 --> 00:54:35,572
Chinese yams are rather slimy.

1473
00:54:35,639 --> 00:54:38,174
-I'm Genie for Chinese Yam.
-He's seasoning it.

1474
00:54:38,241 --> 00:54:39,442
TSUYU

1475
00:54:39,509 --> 00:54:41,945
He's using <i>tsuyu</i>… You're using that much?

1476
00:54:42,012 --> 00:54:44,748
-Is that iced water?
<i>-Tsuyu</i>, lemon juice, and iced water.

1477
00:54:44,814 --> 00:54:45,915
OKRA

1478
00:54:45,982 --> 00:54:49,419
PREPPING OKRA BY BLANCHING

1479
00:54:49,919 --> 00:54:51,821
SHARPEN A DULL KNIFE, THEN CHOP

1480
00:54:52,889 --> 00:54:53,723
It looks spicy.

1481
00:54:53,790 --> 00:54:55,859
-Garlic.
-He's slicing the garlic really thin.

1482
00:54:55,925 --> 00:54:57,560
GREEN ONION

1483
00:54:57,627 --> 00:54:59,629
He's using Thai chili too.

1484
00:55:00,664 --> 00:55:02,799
HO-YOUNG CHOOSES CILANTRO!

1485
00:55:02,866 --> 00:55:04,000
Is that cilantro?

1486
00:55:04,067 --> 00:55:05,302
Yes, it's cilantro.

1487
00:55:05,368 --> 00:55:08,605
-What's that? Flour?
-Flour. Or frying powder.

1488
00:55:08,672 --> 00:55:10,006
I think he'll deep-fry that.

1489
00:55:10,073 --> 00:55:11,107
2. ADD HOG MAW TO CILANTRO BATTER

1490
00:55:12,208 --> 00:55:13,209
He peels the Chinese yam.

1491
00:55:13,276 --> 00:55:15,979
Will he make thin slices?

1492
00:55:16,046 --> 00:55:18,815
He'll peel it into thin slices,

1493
00:55:18,882 --> 00:55:20,717
then julienne the slices
into thin noodles.

1494
00:55:20,984 --> 00:55:22,352
AMAZED

1495
00:55:22,419 --> 00:55:24,120
He said he'd make noodles and fritters.

1496
00:55:24,187 --> 00:55:26,923
How does he do that
despite the slimy texture?

1497
00:55:26,990 --> 00:55:28,491
It's tough

1498
00:55:28,558 --> 00:55:30,427
for chefs in Western cuisine
to shave like that.

1499
00:55:31,094 --> 00:55:32,962
Chefs in Japanese cuisine
are good at that.

1500
00:55:33,029 --> 00:55:35,398
-It's so thin.
-I see.

1501
00:55:35,465 --> 00:55:36,800
They're both making thin pieces.

1502
00:55:36,866 --> 00:55:39,469
He's making thin slices of green onion.

1503
00:55:39,536 --> 00:55:41,071
It's so thin.

1504
00:55:41,137 --> 00:55:43,640
It's as thin as a needle.

1505
00:55:44,140 --> 00:55:46,509
THE PROFESSIONAL CHEFS' STRIKING BATTLE

1506
00:55:46,576 --> 00:55:49,913
Ho-young's slice won't even break off.

1507
00:55:49,979 --> 00:55:51,481
It just broke off,

1508
00:55:51,548 --> 00:55:53,616
-as soon as I said it.
-It's your fault.

1509
00:55:53,683 --> 00:55:55,318
He heard you.

1510
00:55:55,385 --> 00:55:57,420
He was also surprised.

1511
00:55:57,487 --> 00:55:58,855
The green onion slices are so thin.

1512
00:55:58,922 --> 00:56:01,024
Chef Nam-no's knife

1513
00:56:01,091 --> 00:56:02,459
reminds me of him.

1514
00:56:02,525 --> 00:56:04,761
It has a short yet wide blade.

1515
00:56:04,828 --> 00:56:07,263
It's pretty wide. How is it so short?

1516
00:56:07,330 --> 00:56:08,465
Is that for domestic use?

1517
00:56:08,531 --> 00:56:09,833
And so is his apron.

1518
00:56:09,899 --> 00:56:11,568
Yes, the apron too.

1519
00:56:11,634 --> 00:56:12,502
It looks too tight.

1520
00:56:12,969 --> 00:56:15,538
1. PUT GREEN ONION IN WATER
TO REMOVE THE SPICINESS

1521
00:56:15,605 --> 00:56:19,342
Ho-young makes noodles
with the Chinese yam.

1522
00:56:19,409 --> 00:56:20,810
-Thin slices.
-How cool.

1523
00:56:20,877 --> 00:56:22,145
He's using his technique.

1524
00:56:22,212 --> 00:56:25,115
But you know,
I wouldn't call those noodles.

1525
00:56:25,181 --> 00:56:26,516
They're too short.

1526
00:56:26,583 --> 00:56:29,152
-I thought he'd cut it lengthwise.
-Right?

1527
00:56:29,219 --> 00:56:30,487
That's just julienning.

1528
00:56:30,553 --> 00:56:33,022
Yes, we call that julienning.

1529
00:56:33,089 --> 00:56:36,126
But if he decides to call them noodles,
I guess they're noodles.

1530
00:56:36,459 --> 00:56:37,927
MR. SCHOOLTEACHER?

1531
00:56:37,994 --> 00:56:39,963
-The noodles…
-He says shush.

1532
00:56:41,030 --> 00:56:43,800
I would call them noodles
if they're longer, but they aren't.

1533
00:56:43,867 --> 00:56:46,436
He's making them look
similar to his physical traits.

1534
00:56:46,503 --> 00:56:48,004
What can he do?

1535
00:56:48,071 --> 00:56:49,239
That's what he does.

1536
00:56:49,305 --> 00:56:50,707
For a second, I almost said

1537
00:56:50,774 --> 00:56:53,576
the humor of this show
is similar to that of Girls' Generation.

1538
00:56:53,643 --> 00:56:55,078
Yes, we do that too.

1539
00:56:55,145 --> 00:56:57,480
The closer you become like family,

1540
00:56:57,547 --> 00:57:00,049
-the more you tease each other.
-Yes, we do that here.

1541
00:57:00,116 --> 00:57:01,117
-Yes.
-That's it.

1542
00:57:01,184 --> 00:57:02,352
He can take this.

1543
00:57:02,419 --> 00:57:04,554
-Chinese yam fritters.
-<i>Tsuyu?</i>

1544
00:57:04,621 --> 00:57:05,722
The fritters look good.

1545
00:57:06,589 --> 00:57:07,724
It'll taste amazing.

1546
00:57:07,791 --> 00:57:08,892
Like French fries.

1547
00:57:08,958 --> 00:57:10,360
When you deep-fry Chinese yam,

1548
00:57:10,427 --> 00:57:12,295
does it taste similar to French fries?

1549
00:57:12,362 --> 00:57:14,597
If you deep-fry it slightly,
it retains the crunchiness.

1550
00:57:14,664 --> 00:57:18,435
Only when it isn't cooked thoroughly.
If it is, it'll feel like potatoes.

1551
00:57:19,769 --> 00:57:20,937
He's using meat now.

1552
00:57:21,004 --> 00:57:21,838
What's the cut?

1553
00:57:21,905 --> 00:57:23,173
Tenderloin and strip loin.

1554
00:57:23,239 --> 00:57:24,407
TENDERLOIN, STRIP LOIN

1555
00:57:25,008 --> 00:57:28,645
He's grinding the meat he'll use
to wrap the egg.

1556
00:57:28,711 --> 00:57:31,781
-With breadcrumbs.
-He needs breadcrumbs. Did you have some?

1557
00:57:31,848 --> 00:57:32,916
I'm using perilla powder.

1558
00:57:32,982 --> 00:57:34,617
-What? Perilla powder?
-Perilla powder?

1559
00:57:34,684 --> 00:57:36,085
Perilla powder instead of breadcrumbs?

1560
00:57:36,152 --> 00:57:38,188
-Won't it burn?
-It would burn when deep-fried.

1561
00:57:38,254 --> 00:57:39,255
I've never done it.

1562
00:57:39,322 --> 00:57:40,824
AN IDEA EVEN HYUN-SUK HASN'T HAD

1563
00:57:41,658 --> 00:57:45,962
2. GRIND TENDERLOIN AND STRIP LOIN
IN A FOOD PROCESSOR

1564
00:57:46,463 --> 00:57:51,434
SOY SAUCE FROM JANG-JORIM, GARLIC

1565
00:57:52,001 --> 00:57:53,570
Gosh. My apron.

1566
00:57:53,636 --> 00:57:55,872
Your apron looks weird.

1567
00:57:55,939 --> 00:57:59,442
That apron. It's bothering me so much.

1568
00:57:59,509 --> 00:58:01,277
It's suffocating his body.

1569
00:58:01,344 --> 00:58:04,113
Shouldn't you boil some eggs
to make Scotch egg?

1570
00:58:04,180 --> 00:58:06,850
-I'm using quail eggs.
-Quail eggs.

1571
00:58:06,916 --> 00:58:09,018
Precooked quail eggs.

1572
00:58:09,085 --> 00:58:11,588
He's sticking lemongrass into quail eggs.

1573
00:58:11,654 --> 00:58:13,022
He's using quail eggs.

1574
00:58:13,089 --> 00:58:15,191
4. WRAP QUAIL EGG AND LEMONGRASS
WITH MEATBALL MIX

1575
00:58:15,258 --> 00:58:17,160
The housekeeper's <i>jang-jorim</i>.

1576
00:58:17,227 --> 00:58:18,328
I see.

1577
00:58:18,394 --> 00:58:22,031
He's sticking lemongrass into quail eggs,
then wrapping it with the meat mixture.

1578
00:58:22,098 --> 00:58:25,134
-And you'll coat it with perilla powder?
-That's right.

1579
00:58:25,368 --> 00:58:26,236
HOPEFUL

1580
00:58:26,302 --> 00:58:28,171
The eggs are cooked,
so it won't take long.

1581
00:58:28,238 --> 00:58:30,106
-Just cook the meat.
-You know what?

1582
00:58:30,173 --> 00:58:33,142
I really didn't want
to jump on this bandwagon.

1583
00:58:33,209 --> 00:58:35,078
But isn't the apron choking you?

1584
00:58:35,144 --> 00:58:38,047
-I think it is.
-The apron keeps choking him.

1585
00:58:38,114 --> 00:58:39,716
It keeps getting pulled up.

1586
00:58:39,782 --> 00:58:42,118
-I'll pull it down during the check.
-Help him.

1587
00:58:42,185 --> 00:58:44,587
His apron is pretty much…

1588
00:58:44,654 --> 00:58:46,756
-It's choking him.
-His body is locked like this.

1589
00:58:46,823 --> 00:58:48,258
I feel like it'll fall off.

1590
00:58:48,324 --> 00:58:49,926
I've never worn an apron
that was too small!

1591
00:58:49,993 --> 00:58:52,962
You should've brought one in your size!
What is this?

1592
00:58:53,029 --> 00:58:54,731
He can only move his arms this way.

1593
00:58:54,797 --> 00:58:56,065
He gained a few pounds in the back.

1594
00:58:56,132 --> 00:58:57,033
THE APRON IS INNOCENT

1595
00:58:57,100 --> 00:58:59,335
Isn't that the thing you wear
when you get a haircut?

1596
00:58:59,402 --> 00:59:01,871
I guess you can put on weight
in the back too.

1597
00:59:02,205 --> 00:59:04,474
PERILLA POWDER

1598
00:59:05,742 --> 00:59:06,976
He's deep-frying those.

1599
00:59:07,043 --> 00:59:09,779
It's similar to when you deep-fry
using sesame seeds.

1600
00:59:09,846 --> 00:59:10,680
I'm still not sure.

1601
00:59:10,947 --> 00:59:12,115
PERILLA POWDER

1602
00:59:12,181 --> 00:59:14,884
Ho-young also uses perilla powder.

1603
00:59:15,585 --> 00:59:18,054
They're both using perilla powder,

1604
00:59:18,121 --> 00:59:19,522
but for different reasons.

1605
00:59:19,589 --> 00:59:23,526
People often make sesame sauce,
but I wonder what perilla sauce is like.

1606
00:59:23,593 --> 00:59:26,062
Perilla mayo sounds delicious.

1607
00:59:26,129 --> 00:59:27,797
Can you stir this?

1608
00:59:28,064 --> 00:59:29,299
RECEIVES AN ORDER

1609
00:59:29,365 --> 00:59:31,367
NATTO

1610
00:59:31,434 --> 00:59:34,571
It looks like Chef Ho-young
is making two different sauces.

1611
00:59:34,637 --> 00:59:36,039
Sambal and what?

1612
00:59:36,105 --> 00:59:38,207
Sambal sauce and perilla mayo.

1613
00:59:40,310 --> 00:59:42,378
Sam, what are you quietly
doing over there?

1614
00:59:43,546 --> 00:59:45,782
He's making the natto slimy.

1615
00:59:45,848 --> 00:59:47,584
RETURNING TO WORK IN SILENCE

1616
00:59:47,650 --> 00:59:51,354
-I was wondering what he was up to.
-He sat there sadly with his head down.

1617
00:59:51,421 --> 00:59:53,823
-I wondered what he was up to.
-He continues to help him.

1618
00:59:53,890 --> 00:59:55,358
Ho-young always orders him around.

1619
00:59:55,425 --> 00:59:57,527
-He still helps him.
-"It'd be nice if someone helped."

1620
00:59:57,594 --> 00:59:58,928
He can't escape from him.

1621
00:59:58,995 --> 01:00:00,863
He gets zero time on air
if he doesn't do that.

1622
01:00:02,432 --> 01:00:03,766
Why don't you do it sitting upright?

1623
01:00:03,833 --> 01:00:07,503
Look how sad he looks
with his back to us and his head down.

1624
01:00:08,871 --> 01:00:10,573
-Is this good?
-That's good.

1625
01:00:11,641 --> 01:00:12,976
You haven't started on the soup curry.

1626
01:00:13,042 --> 01:00:14,077
I know.

1627
01:00:14,310 --> 01:00:15,345
STARTING NOW!

1628
01:00:15,411 --> 01:00:17,714
OIL WOK GENEROUSLY

1629
01:00:17,780 --> 01:00:19,882
ADD SPICES FIRST,
CHILI, GARLIC, AND GREEN ONION!

1630
01:00:20,116 --> 01:00:21,050
THINGS SEEM SMOOTH, THEN…

1631
01:00:21,117 --> 01:00:23,553
His apron is bothering me so much.

1632
01:00:23,620 --> 01:00:25,989
I feel like I'm suffocating.

1633
01:00:26,055 --> 01:00:27,523
Are you okay, Nam-no?

1634
01:00:27,590 --> 01:00:28,691
-What?
-How's the apron?

1635
01:00:28,758 --> 01:00:29,659
It's so uncomfortable.

1636
01:00:29,726 --> 01:00:31,594
-It keeps getting pulled up.
-It keeps going up.

1637
01:00:31,661 --> 01:00:32,929
What if it comes up to here?

1638
01:00:32,996 --> 01:00:35,531
He looks like an awful cook!

1639
01:00:35,598 --> 01:00:37,567
-That's…
-Come on!

1640
01:00:37,634 --> 01:00:40,670
Don't you look like that
when you wear a shirt backwards?

1641
01:00:40,737 --> 01:00:42,071
Yes, really!

1642
01:00:42,138 --> 01:00:43,873
You have about seven minutes left.

1643
01:00:43,940 --> 01:00:44,774
It's nicely cooked.

1644
01:00:44,841 --> 01:00:47,043
Does it not limit your movements?

1645
01:00:47,110 --> 01:00:48,645
She wants to know
if it limits your movement.

1646
01:00:49,545 --> 01:00:50,980
Just take it off.

1647
01:00:51,047 --> 01:00:52,882
Hey, the microphone!

1648
01:00:52,949 --> 01:00:53,816
Watch out for that!

1649
01:00:53,883 --> 01:00:56,085
-It's an emergency!
-You're running out of time!

1650
01:00:56,152 --> 01:00:57,787
-It's the apron.
-The clock just ticks.

1651
01:00:57,854 --> 01:01:00,089
It's taking him a while,
but he loses the apron.

1652
01:01:00,156 --> 01:01:01,991
UNLEASHED

1653
01:01:02,058 --> 01:01:04,494
He has broken out of his cocoon
and become a butterfly.

1654
01:01:04,560 --> 01:01:05,995
He's much faster.

1655
01:01:06,062 --> 01:01:07,897
We're more at ease now.

1656
01:01:07,964 --> 01:01:10,066
-Is he deep-frying hog maw?
-Chinese yam fritters.

1657
01:01:10,133 --> 01:01:12,035
-Chinese yam fritters.
-Sounds delicious.

1658
01:01:12,101 --> 01:01:14,037
He knows he makes good fritters.

1659
01:01:14,604 --> 01:01:15,605
ONE MORE!

1660
01:01:15,672 --> 01:01:18,207
CHINESE YAM FRITTER, AND?

1661
01:01:19,075 --> 01:01:20,677
HE'S MAKING TWO TYPES OF FRITTERS

1662
01:01:20,743 --> 01:01:22,011
What's that? Okra?

1663
01:01:22,078 --> 01:01:24,013
It's not okra. It's hog maw.

1664
01:01:24,080 --> 01:01:25,481
-Hog maw?
-Hog maw?

1665
01:01:25,548 --> 01:01:27,817
I'm deep-frying hog maw with cilantro.

1666
01:01:27,884 --> 01:01:29,352
Is it your first time deep-frying that?

1667
01:01:29,419 --> 01:01:32,221
Yes, I've only had hog maw as is,

1668
01:01:32,288 --> 01:01:35,892
-but since Hyo-yeon likes it…
-Are you giving it a try?

1669
01:01:35,958 --> 01:01:36,993
-It's a challenge.
-Yes.

1670
01:01:37,060 --> 01:01:38,061
I wonder what it's like.

1671
01:01:38,127 --> 01:01:41,064
He's deep-frying hog maw
in cilantro batter.

1672
01:01:41,130 --> 01:01:43,666
Nam-no is throwing

1673
01:01:43,733 --> 01:01:47,437
-all the "inside" ingredients into a pan.
-Everything is going in.

1674
01:01:47,503 --> 01:01:49,605
It's an inside paradise.

1675
01:01:49,672 --> 01:01:51,174
JANG-JORIM SOY SAUCE

1676
01:01:51,240 --> 01:01:54,177
Did he add gizzards
without parboiling them?

1677
01:01:54,243 --> 01:01:57,447
-Right away.
-Gizzards may have a funky smell.

1678
01:01:57,513 --> 01:02:00,783
That's why I'm using
lots of garlic and pepper.

1679
01:02:00,850 --> 01:02:02,151
Less than five minutes left.

1680
01:02:02,218 --> 01:02:03,386
Less than five!

1681
01:02:03,453 --> 01:02:05,888
-Five minutes left, Jung-hwan!
-Yes.

1682
01:02:05,955 --> 01:02:07,924
Chef Sung-jun, please get over there.

1683
01:02:07,990 --> 01:02:10,660
Who'll make a more amazing beer snack?

1684
01:02:11,227 --> 01:02:13,930
-I'm waiting to hear from Sung-jun.
-I'm looking forward to it.

1685
01:02:13,996 --> 01:02:15,598
-I heard he came prepared.
-Sung-jun.

1686
01:02:15,665 --> 01:02:17,633
What's that sauce? What is that?

1687
01:02:17,700 --> 01:02:20,603
-Soup curry.
-The curry.

1688
01:02:20,670 --> 01:02:21,904
-I want something.
-The fritter.

1689
01:02:21,971 --> 01:02:23,172
-The fritter.
-The fritter.

1690
01:02:23,239 --> 01:02:24,741
Those are the Chinese yam fritters.

1691
01:02:24,807 --> 01:02:26,576
-Should we try the sauce?
-The sauce?

1692
01:02:26,642 --> 01:02:29,212
This one. The perilla sauce.

1693
01:02:29,278 --> 01:02:32,348
Try Chef Ho-young's sauce.

1694
01:02:32,415 --> 01:02:33,282
-All right.
-Okay.

1695
01:02:33,349 --> 01:02:34,917
-The sauce.
-What's it like?

1696
01:02:34,984 --> 01:02:37,186
-What's it like?
-Will it become her Genie?

1697
01:02:37,253 --> 01:02:38,721
HE WAITED AN EPISODE FOR THIS CHANCE!

1698
01:02:38,788 --> 01:02:39,822
Drunk on Beer, Holler.

1699
01:02:42,925 --> 01:02:44,327
I'm making a list of wishes.

1700
01:02:44,393 --> 01:02:45,461
Hey!

1701
01:02:45,528 --> 01:02:46,562
UNSURE

1702
01:02:46,629 --> 01:02:47,797
Is this right?

1703
01:02:47,864 --> 01:02:49,265
It could've gone better.

1704
01:02:49,332 --> 01:02:51,701
Shouldn't you raise your tone as you go?

1705
01:02:52,068 --> 01:02:53,736
DID HE FAIL YET AGAIN?

1706
01:02:53,803 --> 01:02:55,404
What kind of wishes?

1707
01:02:55,471 --> 01:02:56,739
These ones.

1708
01:02:56,806 --> 01:02:58,274
FLAILING

1709
01:02:58,341 --> 01:02:59,609
These wishes.

1710
01:03:01,077 --> 01:03:03,579
These wishes.

1711
01:03:03,646 --> 01:03:05,448
THE FORMER HWASUEUNWA

1712
01:03:05,515 --> 01:03:07,316
MR. SUCCESSFUL FAN KWON

1713
01:03:07,650 --> 01:03:10,052
NAPOLI MATFIA'S TASTE CHECK PASSES

1714
01:03:10,586 --> 01:03:13,322
NICE TRY, SUCCESSFUL FAN KWON

1715
01:03:13,389 --> 01:03:15,057
You could do it!

1716
01:03:15,324 --> 01:03:17,326
STILL IN THE MOMENT

1717
01:03:17,960 --> 01:03:19,395
INDEED, CHEFS ARE SUPPOSED TO DANCE!

1718
01:03:19,462 --> 01:03:21,197
That's more like it.

1719
01:03:21,264 --> 01:03:22,598
Should I try the fritter?

1720
01:03:22,665 --> 01:03:24,534
He's done frying the Chinese yam.

1721
01:03:24,600 --> 01:03:27,937
-Yes.
-You have 2 minutes and 30 seconds!

1722
01:03:28,471 --> 01:03:29,539
NAM-NO'S SELF CHECK

1723
01:03:29,605 --> 01:03:30,807
Why is it so spicy?

1724
01:03:30,873 --> 01:03:31,874
He says it's too spicy!

1725
01:03:31,941 --> 01:03:33,409
What's the spiciness level?

1726
01:03:33,476 --> 01:03:35,011
The chili is really spicy.

1727
01:03:35,077 --> 01:03:36,779
-Can you try it?
-Should I?

1728
01:03:36,846 --> 01:03:39,382
-He says it's too spicy.
-Chef Sung-jun!

1729
01:03:39,448 --> 01:03:40,383
I can't eat spicy food.

1730
01:03:40,449 --> 01:03:43,452
-Nam-no says it's spicy, Sung-jun.
-Sung-jun.

1731
01:03:43,519 --> 01:03:44,720
He might pay dearly.

1732
01:03:48,090 --> 01:03:49,625
IMMEDIATE REACTION

1733
01:03:49,692 --> 01:03:51,661
-Meatball king.
-It's too spicy.

1734
01:03:52,395 --> 01:03:54,864
HE BEGINS TO PLATE IT ANYWAY!

1735
01:03:54,931 --> 01:03:57,466
What should he do? Add more water?

1736
01:03:57,533 --> 01:03:58,367
I don't know.

1737
01:03:58,434 --> 01:04:00,203
SHOULD I… SHOULD I JUST SKIP IT?

1738
01:04:00,503 --> 01:04:01,904
GIVES UP TASTING IT

1739
01:04:02,338 --> 01:04:05,408
NICE TRY, SUNG-JUN

1740
01:04:06,275 --> 01:04:07,877
MATFIA CAN'T HANDLE SPICY FOOD

1741
01:04:07,944 --> 01:04:10,012
-Is it good?
-It must be spicy.

1742
01:04:10,079 --> 01:04:11,814
Spicy food goes well with beer.

1743
01:04:11,881 --> 01:04:13,382
But not something too spicy.

1744
01:04:13,449 --> 01:04:16,319
-What are you doing?
-Removing the chili.

1745
01:04:16,385 --> 01:04:18,421
-He's removing the Thai chili.
-It's really spicy.

1746
01:04:18,487 --> 01:04:21,557
Hyo-yeon can't sit and watch,
so she's walking up toward them.

1747
01:04:21,624 --> 01:04:24,026
It looks like a perfect beer snack.

1748
01:04:24,093 --> 01:04:25,361
But he says it's too spicy.

1749
01:04:25,428 --> 01:04:26,996
I'm pretty tough.

1750
01:04:27,063 --> 01:04:28,865
Yes, Hyo-yeon is pretty tough.

1751
01:04:28,931 --> 01:04:31,200
She said the sauce I made before
was perfect.

1752
01:04:31,267 --> 01:04:34,136
Don't let Sung-jun's opinion
waver your decision.

1753
01:04:34,570 --> 01:04:35,872
PLATING THE CHINESE YAM NOODLES!

1754
01:04:35,938 --> 01:04:37,340
SHORT AND THIN YAM SLICES

1755
01:04:37,907 --> 01:04:38,941
THE NATTO "SOMEONE" STIRRED

1756
01:04:39,008 --> 01:04:40,042
BLANCHED OKRA

1757
01:04:40,243 --> 01:04:43,179
8. DROP YAM SLICES INTO TSUYU SAUCE,
TOP WITH NATTO, OKRA, THAI CHILI

1758
01:04:43,246 --> 01:04:46,382
I think the Chinese yam noodles are ready.

1759
01:04:46,449 --> 01:04:47,783
Fritters.

1760
01:04:47,850 --> 01:04:49,719
-Fritters.
-Chef Ho-young is almost done.

1761
01:04:49,785 --> 01:04:51,320
-Two minutes.
-Two minutes.

1762
01:04:51,387 --> 01:04:53,522
CHINESE YAM FRITTERS, HOG MAW FRITTERS

1763
01:04:54,957 --> 01:04:57,026
THE FRITTERS ARE DONE!

1764
01:04:57,093 --> 01:05:01,530
Wait a minute. Let's check and see
if the perilla powder is burnt.

1765
01:05:01,597 --> 01:05:02,965
Is it burnt? Does it look nice?

1766
01:05:03,032 --> 01:05:04,033
They're cooked nicely.

1767
01:05:04,100 --> 01:05:06,569
-Nam-no's hands tremble.
-What's that?

1768
01:05:06,636 --> 01:05:09,405
-We had that little table?
-That's cute.

1769
01:05:09,472 --> 01:05:10,439
-How cute.
-That's cute.

1770
01:05:10,506 --> 01:05:11,574
That's so cute.

1771
01:05:11,641 --> 01:05:14,477
Hey, wait! I need to top those
with green onion.

1772
01:05:14,543 --> 01:05:15,745
Green onion! Bring them back!

1773
01:05:16,279 --> 01:05:17,680
CALM

1774
01:05:18,915 --> 01:05:22,351
-One minute left, and Ho-young is done.
-Ho-young is done.

1775
01:05:22,418 --> 01:05:24,720
-Is this okay?
-Nam-no.

1776
01:05:24,787 --> 01:05:26,956
It looks like <i>tteokgalbi</i>
topped with pine needles.

1777
01:05:27,023 --> 01:05:28,824
-He has 35 seconds.
-You have time.

1778
01:05:28,891 --> 01:05:32,128
-You have 30 seconds left.
-Only 30 seconds.

1779
01:05:32,194 --> 01:05:35,965
You can balance out the spiciness
with some butter.

1780
01:05:36,032 --> 01:05:37,333
INTRIGUED

1781
01:05:37,400 --> 01:05:38,234
GETS BUTTER

1782
01:05:38,901 --> 01:05:40,136
You're adding butter now?

1783
01:05:40,202 --> 01:05:41,404
-One more. Hurry.
-Twenty seconds.

1784
01:05:41,470 --> 01:05:42,571
-Twenty seconds.
-Twenty seconds.

1785
01:05:42,638 --> 01:05:44,907
-You don't need it.
-No, it'll balance out the spiciness.

1786
01:05:44,974 --> 01:05:46,409
Should you listen to him?

1787
01:05:46,475 --> 01:05:48,744
-Just two dollops.
-Sung-jun is suddenly helping.

1788
01:05:48,811 --> 01:05:51,447
-I don't think you'll need it. It's fine.
-I do.

1789
01:05:51,514 --> 01:05:52,949
-Sung-jun.
-Should I not use it?

1790
01:05:53,015 --> 01:05:53,849
Ten seconds!

1791
01:05:53,916 --> 01:05:55,651
-Nine. Eight.
-Eight.

1792
01:05:55,718 --> 01:05:57,353
-Seven. Six.
-Seven. Six.

1793
01:05:57,420 --> 01:05:59,355
-Shouldn't you mix it?
-Five. Four.

1794
01:05:59,422 --> 01:06:01,590
He's done! Nam-no is done too.

1795
01:06:02,491 --> 01:06:04,760
Did he just throw some butter in there?

1796
01:06:05,962 --> 01:06:07,330
It does smell spicy.

1797
01:06:07,396 --> 01:06:09,598
-He had to rush it.
-He did.

1798
01:06:09,665 --> 01:06:11,067
I didn't know the chili was so spicy.

1799
01:06:11,133 --> 01:06:12,969
And now, both chefs made dishes

1800
01:06:13,035 --> 01:06:16,505
just for Hyo-yeon
to get Drunk on Beer, Holler.

1801
01:06:16,572 --> 01:06:19,408
Nam-no had a bit of twists and turns

1802
01:06:19,475 --> 01:06:22,411
while he cooked,
trying to take his apron off and such.

1803
01:06:22,478 --> 01:06:24,714
I don't know why, but it was too small.

1804
01:06:24,780 --> 01:06:27,149
-You don't know why?
-You don't know why?

1805
01:06:27,216 --> 01:06:28,484
It's not the apron, is it?

1806
01:06:28,551 --> 01:06:30,619
But he still managed to finish his dishes.

1807
01:06:30,686 --> 01:06:34,490
First, please try Chef Ho-young's dish,
I'm Genie for Chinese Yam.

1808
01:06:34,557 --> 01:06:35,825
CHINESE YAM NOODLES

1809
01:06:35,891 --> 01:06:39,061
SAMBAL MAYO, PERILLA MAYO

1810
01:06:40,429 --> 01:06:42,565
CHINESE YAM AND HOG MAW FRITTERS

1811
01:06:42,965 --> 01:06:47,069
CHEF JUNG HO-YOUNG'S
I'M GENIE FOR CHINESE YAM

1812
01:06:47,136 --> 01:06:49,505
This is the hour
when I usually drink beer.

1813
01:06:49,572 --> 01:06:50,706
Would you like some?

1814
01:06:50,773 --> 01:06:54,410
Cheers to another good day.
Great work today.

1815
01:06:54,477 --> 01:06:56,479
They had to make beer snacks,

1816
01:06:56,545 --> 01:06:59,048
so we'll provide some beer.

1817
01:06:59,849 --> 01:07:01,317
Give me a glass too.

1818
01:07:03,019 --> 01:07:05,621
-He wants a glass.
-Chef Eddie wants some too.

1819
01:07:05,688 --> 01:07:07,923
-This is hers.
-Yes, it's my beer.

1820
01:07:08,290 --> 01:07:09,125
JEALOUS

1821
01:07:09,191 --> 01:07:10,526
-Should I have a sip?
-Sure.

1822
01:07:10,593 --> 01:07:11,694
It's a good day.

1823
01:07:15,464 --> 01:07:16,932
It has to go well with beer.

1824
01:07:16,999 --> 01:07:19,068
Yes, she often has beer
as a late night snack.

1825
01:07:19,135 --> 01:07:20,136
GULPING 5 TIMES

1826
01:07:20,770 --> 01:07:22,238
You're enjoying it so much.

1827
01:07:22,905 --> 01:07:24,040
This is nice.

1828
01:07:25,741 --> 01:07:27,877
-Try the noodles first.
-Okay.

1829
01:07:27,943 --> 01:07:31,380
He threw in everything,
Chinese yam, okra, and natto.

1830
01:07:31,447 --> 01:07:32,982
It looks like thin noodles.

1831
01:07:33,949 --> 01:07:34,884
SLURP

1832
01:07:36,419 --> 01:07:39,121
-Mmm.
-Chinese yam and natto go well together.

1833
01:07:39,188 --> 01:07:42,124
It does have that slimy texture.

1834
01:07:42,191 --> 01:07:44,760
When you slice Chinese yam with a slicer,

1835
01:07:44,827 --> 01:07:47,363
it becomes too smiley
and ruins the texture,

1836
01:07:47,430 --> 01:07:51,133
but a knife can preserve
its crunchy texture too.

1837
01:07:52,334 --> 01:07:53,903
You look very happy.

1838
01:07:53,969 --> 01:07:55,971
-Doesn't she look happy?
-She does.

1839
01:07:56,038 --> 01:07:58,474
When I go to a soba restaurant in Japan,

1840
01:07:58,541 --> 01:08:01,010
there's something I always order
and that is

1841
01:08:01,077 --> 01:08:03,345
-Chinese yam soba.
-Chinese yam soba.

1842
01:08:03,412 --> 01:08:05,981
And I eat that with natto over rice.

1843
01:08:06,048 --> 01:08:09,852
<i>-This is like those two mixed together.</i>
<i>-Both Chinese yam and natto.</i>

1844
01:08:09,919 --> 01:08:12,054
I can probably make this at home.

1845
01:08:12,121 --> 01:08:12,955
You're right.

1846
01:08:13,022 --> 01:08:17,359
I diluted some <i>tsuyu</i>,
then added sourness with lemon juice.

1847
01:08:17,426 --> 01:08:19,962
This is exactly what I love.

1848
01:08:20,029 --> 01:08:23,332
Do the Chinese yam slices work as noodles?

1849
01:08:24,066 --> 01:08:24,900
HMM…

1850
01:08:25,901 --> 01:08:28,471
-Noodles?
-Yes, does it feel like noodles?

1851
01:08:28,537 --> 01:08:30,106
-Honestly?
-Yes.

1852
01:08:30,406 --> 01:08:31,807
NERVOUS

1853
01:08:31,874 --> 01:08:33,242
I should have this ready.

1854
01:08:33,309 --> 01:08:35,678
Please don't.

1855
01:08:35,744 --> 01:08:39,081
If it were a little longer,
I could've probably slurped it,

1856
01:08:39,148 --> 01:08:41,450
which then would've felt like noodles.

1857
01:08:41,517 --> 01:08:43,085
Hmm…

1858
01:08:43,619 --> 01:08:44,887
IT'S AN EMERGENCY

1859
01:08:44,954 --> 01:08:46,255
It's an emergency.

1860
01:08:46,322 --> 01:08:49,725
-Turn it off. What are you doing?
-What are you doing?

1861
01:08:49,792 --> 01:08:50,993
She's drinking it.

1862
01:08:51,060 --> 01:08:51,994
DRINKING THE WHOLE THING

1863
01:08:52,995 --> 01:08:54,230
Mmm.

1864
01:08:54,296 --> 01:08:56,265
-It looks good.
-The flavors will pour inside

1865
01:08:56,332 --> 01:08:58,267
-with the sauce when she drinks it.
-And refreshing.

1866
01:08:58,334 --> 01:09:01,670
The slightly sour and salty sauce

1867
01:09:01,737 --> 01:09:04,607
<i>goes so well with Chinese yam,</i>
<i>natto, and okra.</i>

1868
01:09:04,673 --> 01:09:06,075
It must taste refreshing.

1869
01:09:06,142 --> 01:09:07,243
Next, the fritters.

1870
01:09:07,309 --> 01:09:10,913
I made two sauces,
perilla mayo and sambal sauce.

1871
01:09:10,980 --> 01:09:13,916
-Try it as is, then with the sauce.
-The sauce.

1872
01:09:13,983 --> 01:09:15,551
-He made two sauces.
-Okay.

1873
01:09:15,618 --> 01:09:17,686
A BITE OF CHINESE YAM FRITTER, NO SAUCE

1874
01:09:18,821 --> 01:09:21,257
It shouldn't be overdone.

1875
01:09:21,323 --> 01:09:25,761
As previously mentioned,
it'll feel like potato when overcooked.

1876
01:09:25,828 --> 01:09:27,229
But this was fried properly

1877
01:09:27,296 --> 01:09:29,965
and kept the crunchy texture

1878
01:09:30,032 --> 01:09:31,967
of the Chinese yam.

1879
01:09:32,034 --> 01:09:34,069
I can see that it's still crunchy inside.

1880
01:09:34,136 --> 01:09:35,471
-Right.
-Perilla sauce.

1881
01:09:35,538 --> 01:09:36,505
Perilla sauce.

1882
01:09:37,072 --> 01:09:38,974
-She likes perilla seeds.
-She does.

1883
01:09:39,041 --> 01:09:39,942
YUMMY

1884
01:09:41,477 --> 01:09:43,012
Mmm.

1885
01:09:43,078 --> 01:09:46,015
This perilla sauce is unexpectedly

1886
01:09:46,081 --> 01:09:47,449
gooey.

1887
01:09:47,516 --> 01:09:49,251
-Gooey?
-Was that intentional?

1888
01:09:49,318 --> 01:09:50,753
The mayo…

1889
01:09:50,819 --> 01:09:52,188
Turn that thing off.

1890
01:09:53,455 --> 01:09:55,090
THE EMERGENCY LIGHT GOES OFF

1891
01:09:55,157 --> 01:09:57,193
<i>I mixed perilla powder with mayo</i>

1892
01:09:57,259 --> 01:09:59,828
<i>and seasoned it a bit</i>
<i>with </i>tsuyu<i> and sugar</i>.

1893
01:09:59,895 --> 01:10:03,465
The mix of mayo and the powder
makes it feel like this.

1894
01:10:04,667 --> 01:10:07,269
-As if it's slimy?
-Yes, as if it's slimy.

1895
01:10:07,336 --> 01:10:09,138
The sauce feels slimy.

1896
01:10:09,205 --> 01:10:11,040
-That one is spicier.
-Sambal mayo.

1897
01:10:11,106 --> 01:10:12,641
I'll eat it with a piece of Thai chili.

1898
01:10:13,008 --> 01:10:14,843
TRYING IT THE SPICY WAY

1899
01:10:15,711 --> 01:10:16,879
YUM

1900
01:10:18,480 --> 01:10:19,315
Mmm.

1901
01:10:19,582 --> 01:10:20,616
WHAT'S IT LIKE?

1902
01:10:21,183 --> 01:10:22,218
I like this one a little more.

1903
01:10:22,284 --> 01:10:24,086
-The sambal sauce?
-The spicy one.

1904
01:10:24,153 --> 01:10:25,254
Because it's spicier.

1905
01:10:25,321 --> 01:10:27,623
It's really good
with a piece of Thai chili.

1906
01:10:28,857 --> 01:10:30,859
He made hog maw fritters too.

1907
01:10:30,926 --> 01:10:33,629
What did you deep-fry the hog maw with?

1908
01:10:33,696 --> 01:10:37,066
<i>I added cilantro to the batter</i>
<i>because she said she likes the smell.</i>

1909
01:10:37,132 --> 01:10:39,835
So there's hog maw in here?

1910
01:10:39,902 --> 01:10:40,970
And cilantro.

1911
01:10:41,036 --> 01:10:41,870
CRUNCH

1912
01:10:42,338 --> 01:10:44,640
-That sound.
-He's always good at deep-frying.

1913
01:10:45,007 --> 01:10:46,342
HOPEFUL

1914
01:10:46,408 --> 01:10:47,676
-Is it tough?
-No.

1915
01:10:47,743 --> 01:10:50,546
It's even more tender than squid fritters.

1916
01:10:52,014 --> 01:10:56,018
If you didn't tell me it was hog maw,
I would've thought it was a squid fritter.

1917
01:10:56,085 --> 01:10:56,919
I see.

1918
01:10:56,986 --> 01:10:59,388
But the smell of the cilantro…

1919
01:10:59,455 --> 01:11:00,489
is hard to catch.

1920
01:11:00,556 --> 01:11:02,858
Does cilantro lose its scent
when deep-fried?

1921
01:11:02,925 --> 01:11:05,327
No, the Thai chili killed my senses.

1922
01:11:05,394 --> 01:11:06,528
Oh, no.

1923
01:11:06,595 --> 01:11:09,031
My tongue isn't working properly.

1924
01:11:09,098 --> 01:11:10,699
CILANTRO SCENT HAS BEEN DELETED

1925
01:11:10,766 --> 01:11:12,067
All because of Thai chili.

1926
01:11:12,134 --> 01:11:13,502
As I watch this show,

1927
01:11:13,569 --> 01:11:17,539
I buy an ingredient or two here and there
when I like a particular dish.

1928
01:11:17,606 --> 01:11:19,575
-I see.
-I want to try making them myself.

1929
01:11:19,642 --> 01:11:23,112
And this mix
is something that I want to try making.

1930
01:11:23,178 --> 01:11:25,147
I see. She wants to copy the recipe.

1931
01:11:25,214 --> 01:11:28,817
She continues to enjoy her glass of beer.

1932
01:11:29,952 --> 01:11:33,856
And now, Chef Nam-no's dish.

1933
01:11:33,922 --> 01:11:35,324
<i>Meatball King.</i>

1934
01:11:35,391 --> 01:11:38,527
MEATBALL DEEP-FRIED
OVER HER HOUSEKEEPER'S QUAIL EGGS

1935
01:11:40,929 --> 01:11:43,232
SOUP CURRY FULL OF "INSIDES"

1936
01:11:43,899 --> 01:11:47,903
CHEF NAM-NO'S MEATBALL KING

1937
01:11:47,970 --> 01:11:49,638
Meatball King.

1938
01:11:49,705 --> 01:11:51,440
There is something I missed.

1939
01:11:51,507 --> 01:11:52,574
WHAT IS IT?

1940
01:11:52,641 --> 01:11:54,243
-What did you forget?
-Your apron?

1941
01:11:54,610 --> 01:11:56,578
WELL, THAT TOO…

1942
01:11:56,645 --> 01:11:58,681
It's smoked paprika powder.

1943
01:11:58,747 --> 01:12:00,349
Paprika powder?

1944
01:12:00,416 --> 01:12:02,651
A sprinkle of this
will go very well with beer.

1945
01:12:02,718 --> 01:12:04,420
Ho-young, you can either say yes or no.

1946
01:12:04,486 --> 01:12:05,421
It goes well with beer?

1947
01:12:05,487 --> 01:12:06,689
-It does.
-It's very important.

1948
01:12:06,755 --> 01:12:07,723
-It's important.
-It is?

1949
01:12:07,790 --> 01:12:09,425
-She should enjoy it, so…
-Thank you.

1950
01:12:09,491 --> 01:12:10,459
You almost said no, right?

1951
01:12:10,526 --> 01:12:12,061
He's such a generous guy.

1952
01:12:12,127 --> 01:12:16,532
You can sprinkle it on one,
but not the other, and let her compare.

1953
01:12:16,598 --> 01:12:18,300
Should she grab the lemongrass?

1954
01:12:18,367 --> 01:12:20,102
-It's the handle.
-It wouldn't stay straight.

1955
01:12:20,169 --> 01:12:22,438
-It wouldn't work.
-The one on the back will work better.

1956
01:12:23,939 --> 01:12:25,274
That happens with the meatball.

1957
01:12:25,607 --> 01:12:27,042
CHUCKLE

1958
01:12:27,109 --> 01:12:29,078
MEATBALL EMERGENCY

1959
01:12:29,144 --> 01:12:30,145
What is that?

1960
01:12:30,212 --> 01:12:32,448
The one with paprika powder looks thicker.

1961
01:12:32,514 --> 01:12:33,582
RETRYING WITH THE OTHER ONE

1962
01:12:34,683 --> 01:12:35,984
That one worked.

1963
01:12:36,051 --> 01:12:38,454
-Please try it with a bit of green onion.
-This one?

1964
01:12:38,520 --> 01:12:40,823
I'll throw it in after taking a bite.

1965
01:12:41,857 --> 01:12:42,691
A BITE

1966
01:12:42,758 --> 01:12:43,959
I think it'll be good.

1967
01:12:45,494 --> 01:12:46,895
-Wow.
-The green onion too.

1968
01:12:46,962 --> 01:12:48,030
She said wow.

1969
01:12:48,097 --> 01:12:50,632
You wrapped a quail egg

1970
01:12:50,699 --> 01:12:52,735
-with the meat mixture, right?
-Correct.

1971
01:12:53,235 --> 01:12:54,069
Mmm.

1972
01:12:54,136 --> 01:12:55,804
-Huh?
-It must be good.

1973
01:12:55,871 --> 01:12:57,706
-It's really good.
-It is?

1974
01:12:57,773 --> 01:13:00,776
-It's really good?
-The quail egg is your housekeeper's dish.

1975
01:13:00,843 --> 01:13:03,245
First, the meatball is really good.

1976
01:13:03,312 --> 01:13:05,381
And I really love green onion.

1977
01:13:05,447 --> 01:13:07,750
When I don't have any work,

1978
01:13:07,816 --> 01:13:10,352
I like to throw in
a huge pile of green onion into my food,

1979
01:13:10,419 --> 01:13:12,020
into everything that I eat.

1980
01:13:12,087 --> 01:13:13,589
Does the paprika powder add anything?

1981
01:13:13,655 --> 01:13:16,325
It smells like
it's been grilled over charcoal.

1982
01:13:16,392 --> 01:13:18,494
-It was the key.
-I'm not sure if it's the paprika…

1983
01:13:18,560 --> 01:13:19,528
-You're right.
-…or the meat.

1984
01:13:19,595 --> 01:13:22,131
The paprika is smoked paprika
so it adds that.

1985
01:13:22,197 --> 01:13:23,899
-Was that what you wanted?
-It was.

1986
01:13:23,966 --> 01:13:24,967
That was the intention.

1987
01:13:25,033 --> 01:13:27,803
-I'm glad you remembered it.
-It was important.

1988
01:13:27,870 --> 01:13:30,639
Nam-no saw right through the recipe.

1989
01:13:31,940 --> 01:13:34,943
What's important is that
she needs to crave beer after eating that.

1990
01:13:35,010 --> 01:13:36,912
He was supposed to make beer snacks.

1991
01:13:36,979 --> 01:13:39,548
It's so good
that I want to eat it as a decent meal.

1992
01:13:39,982 --> 01:13:42,151
HAPPY, SAD

1993
01:13:42,217 --> 01:13:43,919
The next one.

1994
01:13:43,986 --> 01:13:45,454
What was this called again?

1995
01:13:45,521 --> 01:13:47,356
-Inside curry.
-Inside soup curry?

1996
01:13:49,691 --> 01:13:51,560
The "in" curry.

1997
01:13:51,627 --> 01:13:54,430
He finished that dish
by throwing in two lumps of butter.

1998
01:13:54,496 --> 01:13:55,764
<i>Sung-jun said it was spicy,</i>

1999
01:13:55,831 --> 01:13:58,033
<i>-so he added butter at the last minute.</i>
<i>-Butter, yes.</i>

2000
01:13:58,767 --> 01:14:00,436
Chef Sung-jun was alarmed.

2001
01:14:01,203 --> 01:14:02,237
It was no joke.

2002
01:14:02,304 --> 01:14:05,274
He threw in two dollops of butter.
Whoa, that's a lot.

2003
01:14:05,340 --> 01:14:06,942
This looks like squid,

2004
01:14:07,009 --> 01:14:09,745
thinly sliced half-dried squid.

2005
01:14:10,312 --> 01:14:12,014
The hog maw.

2006
01:14:12,080 --> 01:14:14,550
He must've removed the smell.

2007
01:14:14,616 --> 01:14:17,519
Will the spiciness suit her taste?

2008
01:14:18,020 --> 01:14:18,954
Mmm.

2009
01:14:20,289 --> 01:14:21,824
It's not spicy at all.

2010
01:14:22,191 --> 01:14:23,625
YES!

2011
01:14:23,692 --> 01:14:24,793
Not at all.

2012
01:14:24,860 --> 01:14:26,495
-Not at all?
-The spiciness…

2013
01:14:26,929 --> 01:14:28,430
SHE TRIES THE SOUP TOO!

2014
01:14:28,497 --> 01:14:29,765
She tries the soup.

2015
01:14:29,832 --> 01:14:32,367
-The soup might be spicy.
-It looks good.

2016
01:14:32,434 --> 01:14:33,735
It's spicy!

2017
01:14:33,802 --> 01:14:34,703
Was that spicy?

2018
01:14:36,104 --> 01:14:38,173
-It's too salty.
-Too salty?

2019
01:14:38,240 --> 01:14:39,942
It's way too salty!

2020
01:14:40,008 --> 01:14:40,876
It's an emergency.

2021
01:14:40,943 --> 01:14:42,144
-Even with the butter?
-He was doing so well!

2022
01:14:42,444 --> 01:14:43,946
EMERGENCY FOR NAM-NO

2023
01:14:44,012 --> 01:14:47,783
-She goes for the beer right away.
-Yes, because it was salty.

2024
01:14:47,850 --> 01:14:49,117
It might be intentional.

2025
01:14:49,184 --> 01:14:50,853
It's too salty to have just the soup.

2026
01:14:50,919 --> 01:14:53,222
-Let me try the gizzard.
-Gizzard.

2027
01:14:53,288 --> 01:14:55,023
-Yes.
-The chicken gizzard.

2028
01:14:55,090 --> 01:14:58,360
-It's a success if it doesn't smell funky.
-The gizzard is important.

2029
01:14:58,427 --> 01:15:00,729
-See if it smells.
-Removing the funky smell is the key.

2030
01:15:00,796 --> 01:15:02,331
-So?
-I'm looking forward to it.

2031
01:15:02,397 --> 01:15:03,499
The gizzard.

2032
01:15:04,500 --> 01:15:06,802
Yes, I wonder what that will taste like.

2033
01:15:06,869 --> 01:15:08,303
Yes, this texture.

2034
01:15:08,604 --> 01:15:10,806
THE TEXTURE PASSES!

2035
01:15:10,873 --> 01:15:14,142
-It's crunchy… No, crisp.
-Crisp.

2036
01:15:14,209 --> 01:15:15,744
Yes, that's it. It's crisp.

2037
01:15:15,811 --> 01:15:17,746
It doesn't have any funky smell.

2038
01:15:19,448 --> 01:15:22,484
-I added lots of garlic and green onions.
-It's a success.

2039
01:15:22,551 --> 01:15:23,986
These dishes

2040
01:15:24,052 --> 01:15:27,890
don't feel too heavy for me
as a bar snack.

2041
01:15:27,956 --> 01:15:29,758
-It's perfect.
-It's perfect.

2042
01:15:29,825 --> 01:15:33,595
Please try Chef Ho-young's dish first.

2043
01:15:33,662 --> 01:15:35,364
I'm Genie for Chinese Yam.

2044
01:15:35,898 --> 01:15:37,199
Mmm. It's good.

2045
01:15:37,266 --> 01:15:38,800
It's good.

2046
01:15:38,867 --> 01:15:40,502
It does make me crave beer.

2047
01:15:40,569 --> 01:15:41,803
The yam is so good.

2048
01:15:41,870 --> 01:15:43,005
The sauce is spicy.

2049
01:15:44,306 --> 01:15:46,808
Ho-young is the best at deep-frying.

2050
01:15:46,875 --> 01:15:48,644
No one can beat him.

2051
01:15:49,311 --> 01:15:51,079
TIFFANY TAKES A BITE
OF CHINESE YAM FRITTER

2052
01:15:52,114 --> 01:15:53,649
Mmm.

2053
01:15:53,715 --> 01:15:54,816
What's the fritter like?

2054
01:15:54,883 --> 01:15:57,085
I like the tension.

2055
01:15:57,386 --> 01:15:58,954
TENSION = TEXTURE

2056
01:15:59,021 --> 01:16:00,289
She makes unique expressions.

2057
01:16:00,355 --> 01:16:03,292
She has a creative way of sharing.
She likes the tension.

2058
01:16:03,358 --> 01:16:04,993
It feels like newly harvested potatoes.

2059
01:16:05,060 --> 01:16:08,397
When it still contains lots of water,
it has a bit of a chew to it,

2060
01:16:08,463 --> 01:16:10,666
-and I can feel that here.
-You're right.

2061
01:16:10,732 --> 01:16:12,067
It's like sweet potatoes.

2062
01:16:12,134 --> 01:16:14,603
-Yes, that's the texture.
-The texture of sweet potatoes.

2063
01:16:14,670 --> 01:16:17,306
-But it tastes like a well-cooked potato.
-Exactly.

2064
01:16:19,041 --> 01:16:22,110
All right. Next, Meatball King.

2065
01:16:22,177 --> 01:16:24,913
-He wrapped quail eggs with meat.
-It's meat.

2066
01:16:25,180 --> 01:16:26,315
WHAT'S THE MEATBALL LIKE?

2067
01:16:27,583 --> 01:16:28,717
Mmm.

2068
01:16:28,984 --> 01:16:30,552
SO?

2069
01:16:30,619 --> 01:16:34,389
-The paprika powder feels a bit spicy.
-It's spicy.

2070
01:16:34,456 --> 01:16:36,258
-Really?
-It can be spicy.

2071
01:16:36,325 --> 01:16:37,659
-She's not good with it.
-She's not.

2072
01:16:37,726 --> 01:16:39,361
But it calls for beer.

2073
01:16:39,428 --> 01:16:43,699
-It does.
-It's shaped like <i>tteokgalbi</i>,

2074
01:16:43,765 --> 01:16:46,335
so you might think
it'll taste Korean, like <i>galbi</i>.

2075
01:16:46,401 --> 01:16:48,370
-But the balance in this flavor…
-Beef jerky.

2076
01:16:48,437 --> 01:16:49,705
It's like American beef jerky.

2077
01:16:49,771 --> 01:16:52,174
-The salty ones.
-Not only does it have jolting saltiness,

2078
01:16:52,240 --> 01:16:54,176
but doesn't the smoky scent

2079
01:16:54,242 --> 01:16:56,345
make it taste like beef jerky?

2080
01:16:56,411 --> 01:16:57,512
-You're right.
-Right?

2081
01:16:57,579 --> 01:17:01,383
And now, please choose the bar snack
that makes you want to get drunk.

2082
01:17:01,450 --> 01:17:03,452
<i>Press one to choose Yoon Nam-no</i>

2083
01:17:03,518 --> 01:17:05,320
<i>and two to choose Jung Ho-young.</i>

2084
01:17:05,387 --> 01:17:06,655
Make your decision

2085
01:17:06,722 --> 01:17:08,290
and press a button!

2086
01:17:09,358 --> 01:17:11,893
-I did.
-You did? All right.

2087
01:17:11,960 --> 01:17:13,762
Who did she choose?

2088
01:17:13,829 --> 01:17:16,598
Let's find out the result. Show us!

2089
01:17:17,866 --> 01:17:19,034
Drunk on Beer, Holler.

2090
01:17:19,101 --> 01:17:22,571
Which dish made her crave beer more?

2091
01:17:22,638 --> 01:17:24,306
Is it Ho-young?

2092
01:17:24,373 --> 01:17:25,841
Or is it Nam-no?

2093
01:17:25,907 --> 01:17:27,442
Who's the winner?

2094
01:17:27,509 --> 01:17:29,678
Show us the result!

2095
01:17:30,712 --> 01:17:31,980
Who won?

2096
01:17:32,047 --> 01:17:33,115
Drunk on Beer, Holler!

2097
01:17:33,348 --> 01:17:34,816
JUNG HO-YOUNG WINS

2098
01:17:35,217 --> 01:17:36,184
I'M GENIE FOR CHINESE YAM WINS

2099
01:17:36,251 --> 01:17:37,719
Jung Ho-young wins!

2100
01:17:37,786 --> 01:17:39,321
Chef Ho-young wins.

2101
01:17:39,388 --> 01:17:41,556
HYO-YEON CHOOSES JUNG HO-YOUNG!

2102
01:17:41,623 --> 01:17:44,593
The difference was just a hair's breadth.

2103
01:17:44,660 --> 01:17:45,994
-Thank you.
-That was close.

2104
01:17:46,061 --> 01:17:49,364
The decision was tough to make,
but you picked Chef Ho-young.

2105
01:17:49,431 --> 01:17:53,435
The dish that had the harmony
of the things I loved the most

2106
01:17:53,502 --> 01:17:57,305
was Chef Ho-young's
Chinese yam, natto, and okra.

2107
01:17:57,873 --> 01:18:00,709
It was right up my alley.

2108
01:18:00,776 --> 01:18:05,047
The sweet and sour sauce
with a hint of saltiness was so good.

2109
01:18:05,113 --> 01:18:07,449
I could probably drink

2110
01:18:08,550 --> 01:18:11,687
up to three cans of beer
with just that dish alone.

2111
01:18:11,753 --> 01:18:14,556
She'll put a star on Chef Ho-young.

2112
01:18:14,623 --> 01:18:16,658
-Congratulations, Ho-young!
-Congratulations!

2113
01:18:16,725 --> 01:18:17,693
Great round.

2114
01:18:17,759 --> 01:18:19,394
This is his third star!

2115
01:18:19,461 --> 01:18:21,997
-Chef Ho-young gets a star from Hyo-yeon.
-Thank you.

2116
01:18:22,064 --> 01:18:23,799
-Congratulations!
-Congratulations!

2117
01:18:23,865 --> 01:18:24,866
All right!

2118
01:18:25,767 --> 01:18:28,103
<i>The one who made</i>
<i>K-culture known around the world.</i>

2119
01:18:29,471 --> 01:18:32,741
The two-time winner of the Academy Awards,
please welcome Director Maggie Kang!

2120
01:18:32,808 --> 01:18:35,010
<i>The choreographer of </i>KPop Demon Hunters,

2121
01:18:35,077 --> 01:18:36,344
-please welcome Leejung!
-Leejung!

2122
01:18:36,411 --> 01:18:39,614
"Soda Pop" has to be
the best work I have yet created.

2123
01:18:39,681 --> 01:18:40,982
She brought the Oscar statuette.

2124
01:18:41,049 --> 01:18:41,983
SEEING IT IN PERSON

2125
01:18:42,050 --> 01:18:43,218
<i>Chef & My Fridge</i> has won.

2126
01:18:43,485 --> 01:18:44,352
LIVING VICARIOUSLY

2127
01:18:44,419 --> 01:18:46,154
The sequel has been confirmed!

2128
01:18:46,221 --> 01:18:48,657
<i>I want to present a new K-food,</i>

2129
01:18:48,724 --> 01:18:50,292
so I want to see such dishes.

2130
01:18:50,358 --> 01:18:51,860
Your name might make it into the credits.

2131
01:18:51,927 --> 01:18:53,395
I need your help.

2132
01:18:53,462 --> 01:18:55,063
<i>The first round</i>
<i>is a two-on-two team round!</i>

2133
01:18:55,130 --> 01:18:56,431
Should we add a bit more water?

2134
01:18:56,498 --> 01:18:57,799
THE CRAZY COUPLE IS BACK TOGETHER

2135
01:18:57,866 --> 01:18:59,367
Can you bring some limes?

2136
01:18:59,434 --> 01:19:00,802
He's ordering him around again!

2137
01:19:00,869 --> 01:19:01,803
THE PRO ASSISTANT RETURNS

2138
01:19:01,870 --> 01:19:03,105
Don't be yourself and do as I say.

2139
01:19:03,171 --> 01:19:04,272
Yes, Chef!

2140
01:19:04,573 --> 01:19:05,941
A PERFECT GROUP DANCE

2141
01:19:06,007 --> 01:19:07,342
AN UNEXPECTED CHEMISTRY?

2142
01:19:07,409 --> 01:19:09,878
<i>This is the first tag team round</i>
<i>of the show.</i>

2143
01:19:09,945 --> 01:19:12,047
Tag! You'll take turns
and cook within 15 minutes.

2144
01:19:12,114 --> 01:19:13,515
Wouldn't it be tough for Jong-won?

2145
01:19:13,582 --> 01:19:14,916
You left a huge mess behind!

2146
01:19:14,983 --> 01:19:16,051
THEIR TEAMWORK IS ALREADY GONE?

2147
01:19:16,118 --> 01:19:17,018
One more!

2148
01:19:17,085 --> 01:19:17,986
You have to go!

2149
01:19:18,053 --> 01:19:19,221
I'll kill you if the meat's uncooked.

2150
01:19:19,287 --> 01:19:20,622
Hey, what are you doing?

2151
01:19:20,689 --> 01:19:22,290
WILL THEY UNEXPECTEDLY GET IN HIS HEAD?

2152
01:19:23,458 --> 01:19:24,426
FACING A HUGE CRISIS

2153
01:19:24,726 --> 01:19:26,228
QUICKLY RELAYING THE GREAT NEWS

2154
01:19:26,294 --> 01:19:27,129
Come on!

2155
01:19:27,195 --> 01:19:28,597
Jong-won is finished!

2156
01:19:28,663 --> 01:19:29,698
WHAT HAPPENED IN THE TAG TEAM ROUND?

2157
01:19:32,834 --> 01:19:33,835
Who's the leader?

2158
01:19:33,902 --> 01:19:34,870
-Me.
-It's me.

2159
01:19:34,936 --> 01:19:35,771
What? Hey.

2160
01:19:35,837 --> 01:19:37,539
-What are you doing? Drop your hand.
-You drop it.

2161
01:19:46,882 --> 01:19:51,686
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
